title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat in butter in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add onions, garlic, carrots, celery and green peppers.
Simmer 10 minutes with the pan covered.
Add beef broth or water with bouillon cubes. Add chopped tomatoes and pepper.
Simmer soup on low heat for 35 minutes.
Add hominy.
Boil hamburger soup 10 minutes more.

title: thai chicken barbecue
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a heavy duty, zip-top plastic bag. Add chicken. Seal bag and marinate in refrigerator at least 4 hours. Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade. Bring marinade to a boil in a saucepan; reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes. Coat grill rack with cooking spray; place on grill over medium-hot coals. Place chicken on rack; grill, covered, 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is done, turning and basting frequently with marinade.

title: spinach and mushroom quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix everything together and pour into pie shell.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Save me a slice!!!

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix the ingredients and place in a fairly deep pan.
Pour sauce over meat loaf and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cough syrup
directions: Boil, slowly, lemon juice for 10 minutes.
Put in glass.
Add glycerin.
Stir well.
Fill glass with honey and stir well.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a fork in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Smooth top.
Bake in a 325° preheated oven for 32 to 35 minutes.
Cool on rack.
When completely cool, sift powdered sugar over to coat.
Cut into squares.
This cake goes together very easily and is meant to be mixed in the pan it's baked in.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove bone.
Cut into small pieces.
Put in baking dish.
Mix soup, broth and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Crumble Ritz crackers over this.
Spoon melted margarine over crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stay in bed stew
directions: Brown stew meat in cooking oil.
Add other ingredients, including liquid from water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Cook at 275 degrees for 5 hours.
Add more liquid, if necessary.
Recipe can be doubled and freezes well.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce and let jell in refrigerator.

title: cow pies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Crisco.
Combine all ingredients. Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Chill.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: crispie crunch stick mix
directions: Mix Crispix cereal, shoestring potato sticks and popped corn in large pan.
Heat oil; add dressing mix, dill lemon pepper seasoning and shake in covered container until mixed.
Pour over dry ingredients in pan and stir until well coated.
Place pan in 200° oven and heat for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in raisins.
Cool and store in airtight containers.
tags: dry Hidden Valley original dressing mix

title: personal pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Split open muffins and put on cookie sheet.
Mix tomato sauce, basil and oregano.
Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons of tomato sauce on muffin halves.
Put 2 slices salami or pepperoni on each.
Sprinkle each with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian breaded steak
directions: In medium size bowl beat eggs and milk; set aside.
In another medium size bowl put bread crumbs, garlic powder and grated Parmesan cheese.
Cut top round steak into desired serving size. Dip steak pieces, one at a time, first into egg mixture; then dip into bread crumbs.
Cook in olive oil until golden brown.
Put in low heated oven while cooking remaining pieces.

title: bow tie pasta
directions: Cook pasta until done.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain pasta and vegetables.
Combine pasta and vegetables with dressing; chill and serve.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix pudding with 1 cup milk; set aside.
Puree Oreos and add margarine to make crust.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Layer all.

title: graham crackers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Spread on the 24 graham crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Chop fine the onion, cucumbers, green pepper and carrots. Mix the sugar, white vinegar, mustard, garlic powder, pepper, salt and parsley. Mix pasta, veggies and dressing and refrigerate 2 days ahead.
Serves 18.

title: pastel party pie(edythe cave's recipe)
directions: Drain thawed strawberries.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Heat to boiling.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot liquid.
Add ice cream and stir until melted.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in berries and pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
This is especially good if ground nuts are added to the pastry.

title: ruth's pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Put pie filling on top (cherry, strawberry, etc.).
Double recipe for 3 pies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Butter 1 1/2-quart baking dish; put in layer of green beans.
Spread 1/3 can of soup over beans. Sprinkle 1/4 of cheese over soup.
Continue in same order, making a total of 3 times, ending with cheese.
Dot with butter.
Add crushed potato chips to top.
Bake until hot and bubbly and browned on top at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and stir well.
Add raisins, coconut and nuts; pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes. Season each slice liberally with salt and pepper. Carefully dip each slice in flour until thickly coated. Fry in hot butter until nicely browned. Drain on paper towels. When all slices are fried and draining, put cream or milk into the skillet. Add 1 tablespoon flour to thicken. Stir in butter and salt and pepper, stirring well. Now put the fried tomatoes in a bowl. Pour the gravy mixture over them. Serve immediately.

title: broccoli waldorf salad
directions: In a large serving bowl, combine the first four ingredients. Drizzle with dressing; toss to coat.
Refrigerate leftovers. Yield: 10 servings.

title: hungarian green beans
directions: In medium saucepan over high heat, in 1 1/2 cups boiling water and salt, heat beans to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook, covered, 12 to 16 minutes longer until beans are tender-crisp; reserve liquid.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes, onions and celery.
Rinse; put vegetables in water with margarine and salt.
Cook on medium heat for 25 to 40 minutes until soft.
Add soup.
Stir.
If soup is too thin, you may add potato flakes to thicken as you desire.
Best when eaten with grilled cheese sandwiches.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until smooth. Set aside. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Set aside.
Pour half the batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle half the sugar mixture over batter.
Repeat procedure. Gently swirl batter with a knife. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Drizzle glaze over cake.

title: dino's cereal treats
directions: Set aside some Dino marshmallows to decorate finished squares.

title: elephant ears
directions: In a large mixing bowl, soften yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, butter and salt.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease surface. Cover; refrigerate 3 hours.
Punch down dough.

title: sesame baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken and place in shallow baking dish.
Pour buttermilk over chicken.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight. Next day, pour off buttermilk and dry chicken with paper towels.

title: fluffy rice and chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup, milk and onion soup mix together.
Add rice and mushrooms (with liquid).
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top. Cover with aluminum foil; bake 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Makes enough for 1 pound chipped ham.

title: mom petersen's chili
directions: Brown beef, onions and green peppers; add tomatoes, beans and seasonings.
Let cook until ready to serve.
The longer it cooks, the better it is.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Use ovenproof clay casserole or heavy Dutch oven type pan.
In olive oil, saute chicken, cut up in quarters.
When browned, remove chicken and gently fry onion, green pepper, garlic and tomatoes. Replace chicken in casserole and add chicken broth or water.

When rice and water begin to boil, cover the casserole and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven or cook 30 to 40 minutes on stove top. Garnish with tiny peas and pimento and add mushrooms, if you like. This is the world famous Columbia Restaurant's "Yellow Rice and Chicken."

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Add boiling hot water to mixture.
Form into patties.
Cook in very hot cooking oil.
Fry until brown, turning as needed.
Cook until golden brown.
Makes approximately 15 patties.

title: southern fried corn
directions: Put all ingredients into frying pan.
Cook corn until tender.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix together and let set at room temperature in a glass jar for 2 to 3 days to sour. It should bubble slightly. After removing 1 cup of starter, feed with the starter mixture every 5 to 7 days. Store in refrigerator in loosely covered glass jar.

title: raisin fried pies
directions: Boil raisins in 1 3/4 cups water for 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, cinnamon and sweetener with remaining water.
Add to raisins, stirring until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add vinegar and butter.
Cool overnight for fried pies.
Make pastry as biscuit dough.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil
sugar,
water,
raisins,
shortening,
cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg for 10 minutes.	Let cool.
Add eggs, flour, oatmeal, soda, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight
before baking.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: pecan surprise
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine everything, except oil.
Bring oil to a boil.
Drop by teaspoon into the oil.
When brown on one side, turn until brown on both sides.
Remove from oil.
Makes 50 hush puppies.

title: simple apple pie
directions: Use a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread apples evenly in dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Trim edges and cut bread in half.
Place cut bread over top of apples (should fit).

title: yummy crackers
directions: Bring to a boil the butter, oleo and sugar. Boil for 3-4 minutes. Lightly oil 2 cookie sheets. Spread the crackers in a single layer on the cookie sheets. Pour the boiled mixture over the crackers and spread out with a spatula.

Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 8-10 minutes. Immediately remove from the cookie sheets and place in paper sacks. (If you leave it on the cookie sheets it will stick) Store in Tupperware.

title: angel hair pasta with lemon and chicken
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions. Toss pasta with butter, lemon juice, parsley, marjoram and garlic powder; add chicken. Season with salt and ground black pepper.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Thicken the first 5 ingredients.
Add the potatoes and black pepper.
Place into greased baking dish; bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt, garlic powder, pepper and parsley.
Rinse chicken and dry.
Dip chicken in butter and roll in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable fantasia
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in artichokes, broccoli and mushrooms.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick; place on broccoli.
Saute bread crumbs in 1/2 cup butter until browned. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Melt margarine in pan; stir in flour, pepper, salt and onion salt.
Gradually add milk or juice from salmon; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; beat slowly into egg yolks; stir in salmon.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry.
Fold salmon into eggs.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pastry pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream or ice cream or serve plain.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Decorate top of pie with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then at 250° until done (about 1 hour).

title: reuben casserole i
directions: Mix sour cream, Thousand Island dressing, onion and sauerkraut well. Put mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Layer shredded corned beef over kraut mixture. Add the shredded Swiss cheese. Top with rye bread crumbs. Drizzle the melted margarine over the top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage and egg brunch casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Prepare a day ahead.
Brown sausage, leaving in nice-sized chunks.
Drain and refrigerate.
Beat remaining ingredients, except bread, until light.
Stir in bread and refrigerate.

title: cream doodles
directions: Stir together the marshmallow creme, peanut butter, and honey.
Then add grated chocolate, raisins, and walnuts.
Stir well and shape into small balls.
Roll balls in the shredded coconut.
Chill well before serving.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well with blender or mixer.

title: "best" cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix by hand.
Put in greased 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until toothpick comes out dry.
Frost immediately after taking out of oven.

title: pina colada slush
directions: In blender intermix all items listed.
Put in large Tupperware container.
Put in freezer.
Spoon in chilled glasses.

title: ice cream brownie bowls
directions: Preheat oven and prepare brownie mix according to package directions folding the Heath bits into the batter.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, according to the directions.
Underbake brownies slightly for a chewier consistency and cool thoroughly.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and flour and beat.
Beat eggs one at a time, buttermilk and vanilla; beat and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: boston beans with pork
directions: Place beans in multi-cooker.
Add water to well cover beans. Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Preheat multi-cooker at 375°.
Brown salt pork.
Add onion and saute lightly.
Reduce heat to 212°. Remove excess fat.
Add soaked beans, brown sugar, salt, molasses, dry mustard and catsup.
Mix well, adding enough water to cover beans.
Cover and simmer 4 to 6 hours or until beans are tender. Add water, if necessary.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bara brith
directions: Soak the fruit in milkless tea overnight.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir in the beaten egg.
Combine together well and spoon into a lined tin.
Bake in a moderate (325°) oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve sliced and spread with butter.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown together noodles, tomatoes or juice, ketchup, salt, pepper and cheese. Mix all and bake in covered dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water and cool.
Mix cheese and sugar.
Whip cream.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into graham cracker shell.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
(Blueberry or cherry pie filling may be spread on top of pie in lieu of crumbs.) Refrigerate.

title: dad's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients;
put into baking dish and top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cook for 30 minutes in a 350 degrees oven.

title: dad's shish kabob marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate lamb or shrimp overnight, turning often.

title: chow
directions: Clean, cut and prepare into bite sized pieces.
Season with salt; cook separately until tender and drain.

title: turkey enchiladas
directions: Place tomatillos in blender container with cilantro leaves, onion, garlic and chile.
Puree.
In medium saucepan, heat 2 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Add puree and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add chicken broth and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer sauce 15 minutes.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peach halves; reserve syrup.
Set peaches aside.
In small saucepan, combine reserved peach syrup, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves.
Simmer syrup mixture, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add peaches and heat through only.
Cool; stir in brandy, if using.
Store peaches in covered container in refrigerator at least 48 hours before serving.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in oblong pan.

title: icicle pickle slices
directions: Cover cucumbers and sweet peppers with ice water, use the 1/3 cup salt and let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the pickles and bring to a boil. Put in hot cans and process for sealing.

title: my mom's carrots
directions: Sliver the carrots, thinner than julienne (3 to 4-inch length).
Slice onion into rings.
Add chopped parsley, garlic powder and enough oil and water to steam the carrots.
Steam until tender and serve.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and brown beef in skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, catsup and spaghetti mix.
Simmer.
Boil spaghetti noodles. Mix cooked noodles in sauce and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: unbelievable cookies
directions: Mix the 3 ingredients together in a bowl and drop by spoonful on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 24 to 36 cookies.

title: alice smith's jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water 5 minutes.
Drain and save 1/2 cup liquid.
Blend shortening, spices and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, creaming thoroughly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add baking soda to the liquid.
Add flour, mix alternately with liquid to creamed mixture; mixing well.
Add raisins and chopped nuts.
Chill.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns and onion together in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
In a saucepan, heat the soup, Cheez Whiz and sour cream together, and pour all over the hash browns.
Mix the corn flake crumbs with the melted butter and spread over the top of the hash browns mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange spiced yams 'n' apples(serves 6-8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish, arrange yams, apples and raisins.
In medium sauce pan combine juice, 20 marshmallows, margarine and cinnamon over medium heat. Cook until marshmallows are melted.
Simmer 5 minutes and pour sauce over yam mixture.
Bake 45-50 minutes or until apples are soft.
Baste after 30 minutes with sauce.
Remove from oven. Arrange remaining marshmallows on top and bake 2 to 3 minutes until marshmallows are soft and lightly brown.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk. Add to whipped topping. Fold in fruits and crumbled cookies.

title: sugar-free orange salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple, oranges, Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Sprinkle jello over all and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: susan's salsa
directions: Put tomatoes in blender with hot peppers.
Blend well.
Stir in other ingredients and blend well together.
This will keep in refrigerator 1 to 2 weeks.
Or put in jars, seal and process. Pints or smaller jars for 15 minutes.
Quart jars for 25 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add eggs and oil, stir until moistened (do not beat).
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and pecans.
Add bananas.
Spoon into greased, floured cake pan (3 layers).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peppy barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Remove and discard cloves.
Use as a basting sauce for grilled meats.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Cool, then add other ingredients. Mix well and put in refrigerator.
This is a delicious main dish for a luncheon.

title: carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of water about 10 minutes. Place carrots and 2 tablespoons water in which they were cooked in a greased shallow baking dish.
Mix together mayonnaise, grated onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spoon sauce over carrots and stir lightly.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Crush Ritz crackers and pour melted butter over crackers. Place half of crackers in bottom of casserole dish.
Cook broccoli as directed on package and add milk.
Pour broccoli and cheese in dish.
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup and add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling; dissolve jello in this and cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale; chill until partially set.
Blend pineapple and sauce; fold into jello.
Put in pan or dish; chill until firm. Blend cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on top.
Bake pecans in butter 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle on top.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done; remove from juice and debone.
Cook noodles in juice until done.
Drain noodles and add chicken, soups, butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix together.
Put in casserole dish and top with cheese; bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serves four to five.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs together.
Add flavoring, milk and potatoes.
Last, add instant pudding and mix well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: baked steak
directions: Mix together; put on cookie sheets or shallow pans.
Cut into squares, roll in flour and fry.
Pour mushroom soup, mixed with water, over top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Mix Bisquick
and
water.
Put	in
a
9 x 13-inch pan. Brown hamburger.	Cool
and
add	sour
cream, mayonnaise and onion. Put
on
top of Bisquick.
Chop 3 tomatoes and 2 green peppers and sprinkle on the hamburger.
Top with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° from 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Fry meats and onion until done; drain.
Shred or cube cheese. Add with Italian seasoning to meat mixture.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add desired toppings to meat mixture and stir.
Spread on bread slices; place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: my mom's mexican dip
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat.
Cut cheese in cubes and put in meat to melt.
Add cans of soup.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: In ungreased square pan, mix together flour, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cocoa and brown sugar over batter.
(Do not mix!)
Pour hot water over batter. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon cake in bowl.
Top with ice cream, sauce and nuts.

title: golden cheese soup
directions: Bring water, butter, corn, carrots, onions and pepper to boil in 3-quart saucepan.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in soup, then milk.
Add Cheddar and Provolone cheese.
Serve when cheese melts.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in ungreased pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake in oven, uncovered, at 350° until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
About 5 minutes before done, lay sliced American cheese over top.

title: christmas spice cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done. Cool before serving.

title: creamy peanut butter frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese, peanut butter and butter until creamy. Gradually add 10x sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Makes about 3 cups frosting.
Refrigerate frosted cake.

title: tommie's honeybun cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil, sour cream, butter and mayonnaise, mix well.
In another bowl, combine brown sugar, cinnamon and granulated sugar.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a greased and floured pan. Sprinkle cinnamon mixture over batter.
Pour remaining batter over and spread.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture over batter.
Bake at 325° for 35-40 minutes.
Prepare glaze by combining powdered sugar, vanilla and milk.
Pour glaze over hot cake.

title: glaze for chocolate bundt cake
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Add powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread while warm over Bundt cake as a glaze.
Will not cover whole cake.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread in pan and bake until golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes.
Cut into small pieces to serve.

title: quick strawberry cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling into a greased 9x13x2 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 5-7 minutes or until heated through.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, cream butter, cheese and vanilla.
Place cake mixes in another bowl and cut in cream cheese mixture until crumbly. Sprinkle over hot filling.	Bake 25-30 minutes longer or until topping is golden brown.
Other pie fillings are good also, but my family like strawberry best.
Serves 12.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook on medium heat until done.
Serve over rice.

title: frozen daiquiris
directions: Mix together and store in covered container in freezer; keeps indefinitely.
Serve frozen in cocktail glass.

title: easy holiday punch
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and fruit juices.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Pour over ice.
Yield:
1 1/4 gallons.

title: old time lemon pie
directions: Heat sugar, water and butter or margarine until sugar dissolves.
Blend cornstarch and cold water.
Add to hot mixture. Cook slowly until clear, about 8 minutes.
Beat egg yolks with milk.
Slowly stir into cornstarch mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice and lemon peel.
Cool. Pour into cooled pie crust.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Cream eggs and sugar; add the rest of ingredients.
Pour mixture into a single unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Delicious and easy.

title: pennsylvania dutch cinnamon flop(breakfast bread or dessert)
directions: Cream tablespoon of butter and sugar together.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Alternate milk and dry mix as you mix into creamed butter and sugar.
Mix until smooth.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Bake at 400° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: nancy drew pork chops or the case of the smothered pork chops
directions: In a casserole dish, pour rice.
Top with browned chops.
Top each chop with onion and pepper.
Pour broth over chops.
Season with lemon pepper.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: sourdough biscuits and pancakes
directions: Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, pepper, salt, onion, garlic powder and onions.
Put in a large skillet and brown.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, pizza sauce and simmer.
Cook noodles until tender. Drain and then layer as follows:
noodles, sauce and meat mixture and pepperoni, repeat first 2 steps and then top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: five minute banana pudding
directions: Melt sugar in a heavy skillet until golden brown.
Pour into a 1-quart souffle dish and tilt it immediately to coat the bottom and sides with caramel.
Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually, until thick and pale.
Heat milk, add flavorings, then slowly pour into egg mixture.
Gently pour into caramelined dish and bake in a pan of hot water at 325° about 1 hour or until set.
Chill, then unmold.

title: chicken picante
directions: In large bowl, make marinade by mixing taco sauce, mustard and lime juice.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Marinate for at least 30 minutes.
In large frypan, melt butter over medium heat until foamy.
Remove chicken from marinade and place in frypan.
Cook, turning, about 10 minutes or until brown on all sides.
Add marinade and cook about 5 minutes more, until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease and marinade is slightly reduced and beginning to glaze.

title: baked hush puppies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl; mix well.
Add buttermilk, onions, egg and hot pepper sauce, if desired; stir until mixed.
Generously butter a 9-inch square baking dish. Shape dough into 16 balls, about 1 heaping tablespoon each.
Roll balls in melted butter; place in prepared dish.
Pour remaining butter over dough balls in dish.
Bake until lightly browned and thoroughly baked in the center, 15 to 18 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Mix well.
Put in casserole and cover with 1/2 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin gingerbread with caramel sauce
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in pecans.

Press 1 1/4 cups mixture into bottom of ungreased 9-inch square pan; set aside. Combine remaining crumb mixture, buttermilk and the next 8 ingredients; beat at low speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Pour over crumb mixture; bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool in pan or wire rack.
Cut into squares; serve with Caramel Sauce and ice cream.
Serves 12.

title: mexican rice and bean soup
directions: Cut links into pieces; brown.
Remove from pan; spoon off all but 1 or 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Add water, juice, beans, rice, sausage links and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until rice is done.

title: southern red beans
directions: Let beans soak for more tender beans and then bring a large boiler of water to a boil.
Pour beans in boiling water.
Turn heat to medium and let cook about an hour.
Chop seasonings very fine, and salt and pepper to your taste.
Boil pig tails at same time until you put the beans on.
Cook pig tails until tender. Fry bacon.
Pour 1/2 grease from bacon into the cooking beans; add pig tails and one stick of butter or margarine.
Cook another hour on low.

title: coconut pie shell
directions: Grease a 9-inch
pie
plate with butter.
Empty coconut into pie plate
and
press
against bottom and sides.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Makes 1 shell.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, salt, and pepper together.
Cut tomatoes in slices 1/4 inch thick. Cover slices of tomatoes with breading mix.
Deep fry in oil.

title: cracker spread
directions: Chop and mix everything to a spreadable consistency with mayonnaise as necessary.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts in salted water with celery and onion pieces for 1 hour.
Best to simmer.
When done, strip meat from bones and cut into serving portions.
Partially cook frozen broccoli.
Butter bottom of baking dish and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over butter.
Line bottom of dish with broccoli.
On this, arrange deboned chicken.
Mix together curry powder and lemon juice.
Combine with cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Pour sauce over broccoli and chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: sauerkraut auf bayische art(bavarian style sauerkraut)
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with warm water 2 times; drain well.
Cook onion and bacon in butter until onion is soft.
Add the drained kraut, caraway seed and sugar.
Cover tightly.
Cook 1/2 hour. Add bouillon and wine.
Simmer 1/2 hour longer or until kraut is cooked to your taste.
Serve as vegetable with sauerbraten of Kalbshaxe, or top with a selection of pork products such as boiled thick slabs of bacon, Bratwurst, frankfurters or Regensburg sausage.
On such a plate, Ernspuree and mashed potatoes are always served.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crock-pot hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs in bite size pieces and mix with other ingredients in crock-pot.
Simmer 6 hours.
Good for parties or barbecue.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until fluffy.
Stir together dry ingredients; then add to pumpkin mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan or large fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kraft macaroni and cheese salad
directions: After macaroni is cooled, add all ingredients. Mix well. Chill before serving.

title: corn chowder
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a Dutch oven.
Add the sausage, onion and celery.
Saut until the vegetables are tender.
Add the potatoes.
Add enough water or chicken stock to cover completely. Simmer, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add the corn and stir to mix.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add the half and half. Cook until almost at the boiling point.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a small skillet.
Add the flour.
Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Whisk the flour mixture (roux) into the chowder.
Cook over medium-high heat until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve in individual bowls or a tureen.
Sprinkle with the parsley.
Serve with Fried Tortilla Strips, if desired.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Bring all but popcorn to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Mix with popcorn and bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: mom flowers' corn fritters
directions: Mix corn, egg and flour together.
Add dash of pepper and salt, if desired.
(Make sure mixture isn't soupy.)
Deep fry on high until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Skin chicken breasts and place in bottom of crock-pot.
Mix together all remaining ingredients, draining mushrooms; pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Goes well with rice.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: homey's no fuss beef and spinach lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Season beef with salt; stir in spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and red pepper.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, spinach, Parmesan cheese and egg.
In a 13 x 9-inch or bigger pan, spread 2 cups beef sauce over bottom.
Arrange 4 noodles lengthwise in single layer.
Place noodles and press into sauce.
Spread entire cheese mixture over noodles; sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and top with 1 1/2 cups beef sauce.
Be sure to cover all the noodles with sauce.
Layer noodles and cheese and beef sauce!
Cover noodles!
Tent with foil.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve !

title: german coffee cake
directions: Mix scalded milk, lard, sugar, salt and 1 1/2 cups water (should be lukewarm).
Add yeast that has been dissolved in the warm water; stir well.
Add flour and knead until dough isn't sticky.
Roll thin and spread with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar after the dough has been brushed lightly with butter.
This dough can be made in jellyroll pans, small cake pans, made into cinnamon rolls, etc.
Let rise.
Add a little more cinnamon and sugar; bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions. After cake is done, poke holes all through cake with a straw. Mix pudding according to directions. Drain pineapple and add to pudding. Spread pudding mixture over hot cake. Let cool and ice with Cool Whip.

title: muskogee pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add sugar, syrup, butter or margarine, vanilla and salt, one at a time, beating each until blended. Spread pecan halves evenly in the unbaked pie crust.
Slowly pour filling into pie shell.
Cover the edge of pie crust with strips of aluminum foil and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
When a toothpick comes out clean, the pie is done.
Not as rich as most; eat all you want.
A great dessert "Okie style."

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Combine ingredients, stirring over low heat.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before cutting into squares.

title: hamburger cheese chowder
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion together.
Salt and pepper.

title: adam's chicken duke
directions: Roll chicken in flour, meal, parsley, salt, pepper and ginger. Fry in oil with onion, clove of garlic and soy sauce.
Brown both sides of boneless chicken breasts.
Add enough chicken broth to cover.
Sprinkle with extra flour and soy sauce to make brown.
Put in skillet, cover and cook until done.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix sugar, water, vinegar and spices.
Boil 5 minutes.
Slice beets and add to boiling syrup.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pack in 4 pints.
Seal.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.
A small amount of sugar may be added to sour cream, if desired.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Cook the macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender; drain.
Melt one tablespoon butter in a saucepan.
Saute onion until golden brown.
Blend in soups and cream, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add chicken, carrots and peas and simmer, covered over a low heat, for 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and form into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Place peanut butter balls on toothpicks and dip in chocolate mixture.
Drop onto wax paper and let dry.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Start oven at 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Wash eggplant, pare and cut in thick slices.
Dip each slice into beaten eggs, and then into crumbs.
Saute in hot oil in skillet until golden on both sides.
(Eggplant will be soft.)

title: carrot juice(fresh)
directions: Clean, wash and prepare all veggies for an electrical juicer. Drink at room temperature or slightly chill.
Great as a breakfast drink with a bagel or toast.
Or as an evening cocktail.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour into casserole over melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: venison
directions: Cut all skin, membrane and gristle from venison.
Place in Brown-in-Bag.
Sprinkle venison with onion soup mix, pepper and red wine vinegar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 2 hours.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts.
Let chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Open beans and drain; put into casserole.
Add mushroom soup diluted with warm milk.
Bake in a moderate oven 20 minutes. Remove from oven; spread onion rings on top of beans and press down lightly.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes.

title: vena's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and season with oregano, salt and basil.
In large kettle, add tomato paste or puree and water.
Bring to boil, lower heat and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer about 4 hours, stirring often (careful so sauce does not stick to bottom of pan).

title: caramel apple bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add flour, oats, salt, soda and pecans.
Mix well.
Set aside 2 cups. Press remaining into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Toss apples and flour together.
Spread in pan.
Melt caramels and margarine over low heat (or microwave).
Drizzle over apples.
Top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Combine soups, sour cream and corn (drained).
Place egg noodles in casserole.
Mix the ingredients with the noodles.
Top with cheese (optional) and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meat balls(appetizer)
directions: Mix all ingredients into little balls (about 1 to 1 1/2-inches in diameter).
Bake in oven for approximately 20 minutes at 375°. When meat balls are done, cover with 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can milk mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; mix well.
Mix flour, salt and cocoa.
In a separate bowl, mix milk, vanilla and food coloring.
Add these alternately to mixture.
Put vinegar and soda in a cup; mix well.
Add immediately to mixture and fold in. Makes three 8-inch layers.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon 10 minutes.
Add celery and onions and cook until tender. Add butter; wait until butter is melted. Add flour. Stir to cover all ingredients. Add packets of chicken broth, clam juice and clams.
Stir and bring to a boil, then add potatoes. Cook until tender, about 20 minutes on simmer.
Add Farm Rich cream. Chowder should be on the thick side.
(Start this chowder in a large pot.)

title: cajun rice
directions: Chop and saute in butter the garlic, celery, pepper and onion. Boil rice.
Stir together sauteed vegetables, rice, tomatoes and soup.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Spray 4 (1 pound) coffee cans with Pam.
Pour batter 1/2 full in cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 3 to 4 minutes, then turn out of cans.
When completely cool, put back in cans.
Store with lids on.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening;
add eggs and mix thoroughly. Stir soda into milk mixture; add milk mixture alternately with flour
and	mashed	bananas
to
shortening.
Add
nuts. Grease 2 loaf pans;	add mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. When butter knife comes out clean, bread is done. Remove from pans and
cool
on wire rack.
May be frozen for 1 month.
Great for any holiday!

title: french bread
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients to lukewarm.
Beat all the above ingredients for 2 minutes.
Add 2 more cups flour and beat 2 minutes more.
Now, stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough (usually about 1 1/2 more cups).
Knead about 8 minutes.
Let rise in bowl.
Then turn out on floured counter and let rest about 20 minutes.
Shape into 3 long loaves; place on greased baking sheet and let rise until double.
Then bake at 375° about 30 minutes.
If you like a harder crust, bake 45 minutes.

title: zucchini crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into cakes.
Roll in flour and fry (in oil) until browned on both sides.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Mix eggs, salt, pepper, milk and cheese.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish and bake at 300° for about 30 minutes, then turn oven up to 400° for a few minutes to brown top lightly. Serves 8.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, eggs, bread crumbs, catsup, water and soup mix thoroughly.
Put in meat loaf pan.
Top with bacon if you like. Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
Then add vanilla.
Fold in chips and pecans.
Line cookie sheets with tin foil.
Place 1 tablespoon of cookie mix on sheet for each cookie.
They will not rise.
Turn the oven off and place cookies sheets in the oven.
Do not open the door until the next morning.
Carefully remove cookies from foil lining and store in covered container.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecan halves and cherries in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Add pecan halves and cherries on top to decorate.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly.
Add other ingredients. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.
Good with potato chips and pickles.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Put toast into a greased 1 1/4-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins over toast.
Combine eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla; pour over toast.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a tube pan.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Melt semi-sweet morsels, margarine and peanut butter in large saucepan.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Heat and stir until sugar is dissolved, being careful not to overcook.
Add oatmeal; stir and drop spoonfuls on wax paper to dry.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cut cheese into thin slices.
Cut donut holes from bread; set aside.
Place remaining bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer cheese over bread; layer of broccoli; layer of ham.
Arrange donut holes on top.
Combine milk, onion, salt and mustard; pour over bread.
Cover; refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 65 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more; let stand for 10 minutes.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Place in casserole.
Cover with green beans.
Pour soup over beans.
Arrange Tater Tots in single layer over top.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour or until potatoes are browned.

title: guacamole dip #2
directions: Combine and chill all ingredients.
Serve with cubed Monterey Jack cheese.
Use fancy toothpicks and spear each piece of cheese. Your guests will thank you for doing that.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: This recipe is also good with chicken breast.

title: brownie meltaways
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownies as directed on package except stir coconut and nuts into batter.
Bake as directed; cool. Mix powdered sugar, 1/3 cup margarine and vanilla.
Stir in milk, 1 teaspoon at a time, until spreading consistency.
Spread over brownies.
Refrigerate until topping is firm, about 30 minutes. Heat chocolate and 2 teaspoons margarine until melted.
Drizzle evenly over topping.
Spread evenly.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes. Remove and cut into squares to prevent chocolate from cracking. Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Cut bacon into small pieces; cook and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: apple stuffed pork shoulder
directions: Cook onion in butter or margarine until golden brown.
Combine with remaining stuffing ingredients.
Set oven for moderate 350°. Fill pocket in pork shoulder with stuffing.
Fasten with white twine.
Place pork on rack in open roaster.
Roast approximately 40 minutes per pound.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix well. Let sit in the fridge a few hours. Dip fresh vegetables.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix wet ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients, then combine with wet ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mary ann's tomato, onion, cucumber salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a jar; shake well.
Into a large bowl, put a layer of tomatoes, a layer of cucumber and a layer of onion.
Pour first 6 ingredients over this.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Hers was delicious!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread out the rolls.
Brown sausage and spread over rolls.
Pour cheese over sausage.
Mix together the eggs and milk.
Pour over cheese. You can refrigerate overnight.
Bake in oven 40 minutes or until eggs are set.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; add sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Thoroughly cream first 6 ingredients.
Sift together flour, soda and spices.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Chill well.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with a gingerbread boy cutter or draw your own pattern.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle lightly with granulated sugar for sparkle.
Trim with red cinnamon candies. Bake in 375° oven for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove to rack to cool.
Makes 6 dozen 4-inch gingerbread men.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thickens.
Let cook and let pie crust cool, then pour into pie shell.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, raisins, coconut, nuts and flavoring.
Add eggs and butter.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash.
Add onion, soup and sour cream.
Pour dressing in casserole, saving some for topping.
Pour squash mixture on top of dressing and top with reserved dressing.
Top with cheese and bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: 1. Bring broth to boil. Add pasta and cook as per directions.
2. Mix eggs and cheese. Add to broth and pasta at a boil.
Stir in well and cover. Remove from heat.

title: salt rising bread
directions: Scald milk.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add sugar, shortening, salt and corn meal.
Place in quart fruit jar.
Set in water, 120°.
Let stand 6 to 7 hours until fermentation can be noted.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour to make sponge.
Beat vigorously.
Set the sponge in water, 120°, until very light.
Add remaining flour to make dough stiff enough to knead.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Place immediately in greased baking pan.
Let stand until double in bulk and bake.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
This is heavier than other bread.
Makes very good toast.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, half the tomato sauce, egg, 1/2 teaspoon oregano, salt and pepper.
On wax paper, pat into rectangle 1/2-inch thick; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Roll up by starting on short side.
Lift paper until meat begins to roll tightly.
Peel back paper to keep it free.
Continue lifting and peeling to complete roll.
Seal edges and place in loaf dish.
Microwave at High 9 minutes, rotating dish after half the cooking time.
Reduce power to 50% (Medium).
Microwave 11 to 14 minutes, or until meat loses most of its pink color, rotating dish after half the cooking time.
Drain.
Combine remaining tomato sauce and oregano.
Pour over meat loaf.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Microwave 2 minutes to heat sauce.
Tent with foil and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cheesy rigatoni bake
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Layer apple slices in pie shell.
Mix apple juice, cinnamon, nutmeg and cornstarch in saucepan; cook on low heat until thickens. Pour over apples.
Place second pie shell on top, lightly butter on top of shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Makes one double crust pie.

title: date balls
directions: Cook butter, sugar and dates over low heat until thick. Remove from heat.	Add
nuts
and	vanilla
and return to heat until alcohol evaporates from vanilla (about 30 seconds).
Add Rice Krispies and
stir,
then
cool.
Make
into
balls
and lightly roll
in
powdered sugar.
Store in covered, air-tight container.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend with wire whisk.
Melt oleo in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in cocoa and sugar; mix well.
With wire whisk, stir in egg mixture a little at a time until blended.
Pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: corn pudding bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix all together.
Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Remove skin and fat from meat.
Cut meat across grain in narrow strips.
Heat butter in large heavy pan.
Add meat and cook stirring with a fork until brown.
Add onion and continue cooking 2 or 3 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over meat and stir well.
Add consomme and soup, cook stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens.
Add drained mushrooms and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream and paprika.
Add additional salt and pepper if needed.
Serve over noddles or rice.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make pudding as directed and chill.
Bake cake in 2 layers and cool.
Cover bottom of punch bowl with sliced strawberries.
Put 1 layer of cake.

Spread 1/2 of pudding, 1/2 can pineapple with juice, 2 1/2 sliced bananas, 1 layer of cake, sliced strawberries with juice (save 1 whole strawberry), spread 1/2 of pudding, 2 1/2 sliced bananas and 1/2 can pineapple with juice.
Puncture holes in cake with wooden spoon handle all the way to bottom of bowl.
Top with Cool Whip.
Spread generously with spatula.
Sprinkle with coconut (Walnuts optional).
Top with 1 whole strawberry in center.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Slice peeled potatoes and add onion. Add just enough water to barely cover potatoes and onion. Cook until done. Mash potatoes in their juice. (Do not drain off water.) Add butter and milk; let simmer about 10 to 15 minutes more. Sprinkle with parsley flakes. If too thick, add a little water.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Melt cheese and add all other ingredients; blend well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugars gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Mix and add in eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: favorite sherbet(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Mix the sugar and water; boil 5 minutes, then cool.
Add the juice of the lemons and oranges, then the crushed bananas.
Freeze to a mush and then fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites and continue freezing until firm.

title: no peek beef stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, first place beef chunks on bottom, then a layer of each vegetable and the juice.
Add seasonings to sugar and tapioca.
Pour over juice.
Cover and bake at 225° for 4 to 5 hours.
The liquid will thicken by itself while cooking and acts as a tasty gravy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into glass bowl.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Drain.
Place in serving bowl.
Spear with wooden skewers.

title: clam chowder of the tribes from northeast coast
directions: Brown the bacon in a large saucepan; add the onions and saute until golden.
Chop the clams; drain and save liquid.
Add the clams to the kettle, then mix in the butter and flour.
Heat, stirring for about 2 minutes.
Stir in the clam juice and water, then add the potatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and set aside. Melt butter and add remaining items.
Stuff mushrooms and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Can make a day ahead of time.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well and sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° until brown about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: recipe for a happy life
directions: Carefully combine all ingredients, saving 1 cup laughter and 1 cinnamon stick.
Use cinnamon stick to gently stir ingredients. After carefully mixing, top with the 1 cup laughter you saved. Recipe serves everyone.
Guaranteed to make you feel great.

title: cough syrup
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose one too young and take one that has been reared in a good moral atmosphere.
Do not insist on keeping them in a pickle or keeping them in hot water. This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.

Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste, then wrap them in a mantle of charity, keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream. When prepared thusly, they will keep for years.

title: mexican tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat butter and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour and nuts, beating until well mixed. Refrigerate until firm, about 30 minutes.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly browned on bottom.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown onion and hamburger in skillet.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix as directed on package.
In large pot, combine all ingredients.
Heat until warm; allow to simmer.

title: chicken, cheese 'n' biscuits(weight watchers)
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot; add flour, mustard and sage and stir quickly to combine thoroughly.
Stirring constantly, gradually add milk; continue to stir and cook until smooth.
Add broth mix and pepper and mix well.
Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture is thick, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cheese and cook, stirring, until melted.
Add chicken and vegetables and continue cooking until chicken and vegetables are heated through, 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: irene's quick peanut-butter pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust.
Drizzle hot fudge sauce on crust.
In mixing bowl with electric mixer, mix cream cheese, peanut butter and milk.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler or microwave in a large bowl. Add oil and sugar.
Blend. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each. Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and stir into chocolate mixture. Add nuts. Chill several hours or overnight.
Shape into small balls. Roll in powdered sugar and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: gramma willson's lemon pie filling
directions: Cook on top of stove over low heat until thick.
Pour into baked or graham cracker pie crust.
Top with meringue, if desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Then put in 1 cup sugar and let stand for 1 hour.
Dissolve cherry jello in 2 cups hot water and add 1 cup cold water.
When jello is cool, add cranberries and crushed pineapple; add diced grapes; add ground celery and chopped nuts.
Stir.
Let set until firm.
Put milk in double boiler with marshmallows until melted.
Let cool and add whipped cream (sugar and vanilla) and creamed cottage cheese.
Spread this on top of jello cranberry salad.

title: summer's pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar by spoonfuls and continue beating.
Fold in baking powder, pecans, cracker crumbs and vanilla.
Pour into one buttered pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: easy cheesy manicotti
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Lay flat on foil to cool.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: pasta and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender in salted water.
Remove cauliflower and put aside.
Cook spaghetti in the cauliflower water.
Meanwhile, saute olive oil and the garlic in a pan.
When cooked, put aside.
Drain the spaghetti; add salt, cauliflower, oil, garlic and 1/2 cup cheese.
Toss and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain oranges, reserving and measuring liquid.
Add 1 1/2 cups of drained orange liquid to the jello.
Stir in the sherbet until dissolved and refrigerate until partially set.
Peel and slice bananas and add to the thickened jello along with oranges.
Pour into 6-cup mold or square dish and chill until set.
Serves 6.

title: different sweet potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes and apricot juice (save enough to make 1 1/4 cup liquid).
Dice potatoes into bite size pieces.
Arrange in layers of potatoes, apricots and nuts.
Mix dry ingredients in saucepan.
Over low heat, slowly add apricot juice.
Stir until thick.
Add margarine and pour over layered ingredients.
Heat 25 to 35 minutes at 375° (9 x 13-inch casserole).
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix with sausage and Bisquick.
Make into balls (about 1 or 1 1/2-inches thick).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Put crackers in brown paper bag; mix oil, dill weed and dressing mix together.
Pour over crackers in bag.
Shake bag, then shake again every 10 minutes for 1/2 hour.
Set bag in sink as it gets greasy.
Store in airtight container.
Keeps well.

title: porkie pine balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using just one can of tomato sauce.
Shape into balls.
Mix 2 cans tomato sauce and 2 cans water in skillet and heat.
Add the balls.
Simmer for 30 to 35 minutes at 250°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together corn, eggs, corn meal, garlic powder and oil. Pour 1/2 mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of grated cheese.
Spread green chilies over cheese.
Pour remainder of corn mixture over green chilies, then remainder of cheese on top.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Allow to cool 20 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: refried bean casserole
directions: Spread refried beans in casserole dish.
Sprinkle chopped onion and bell pepper over the top.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and juice to this and sprinkle grated cheese over the top.
Heat in a 350° oven until hot throughout and cheese is melted.
Crumble Doritos and add to each serving.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat all together, pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes or until done.
Start at 350° for 5 or 10 minutes, then reduce to 300° and bake about 40 minutes.

title: mary's seafood pasta
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed on the box.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Then add shrimp and toss for several turns. Drain spaghetti and add to the pepper and shrimp.

title: yam cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. In a large bowl, cream sugar, 1 cup margarine and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Cut up yams; add to creamed mixture, beating until well mixed. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Add flour, cinnamon soda and nutmeg. Mix well. By hand, fold in pecans, raisins and drained pineapple. Spoon batter into prepared pan. Spread evenly. Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted
in center comes out clean. Cool upright in pan 10 minutes. Invert onto serving plate. Cool completely.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in one bowl and wet; including carrots, raisins and nuts in another bowl.
Combine the two mixtures and blend only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overbeat. Fill buttered muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Yields:
20 to 24 muffins.

title: blueberries n' cream cheesecake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in container of an electric blender; cover and process on high speed until smooth.
Cook blueberry mixture in a saucepan, over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, about 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Set to cool, reserving 1/2 cup for glaze.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy; gradually add 1 cup sugar beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in 2 tablespoons cornstarch and salt.
Pour into a greased 9-inch spring-form pan. Pour blueberry mixture over cheesecake batter, gently swirl with a knife.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven and cool on a wire rack 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato, carrot, ginger soup
directions: Cook chopped onion in oil over medium high heat for 5 minutes. Stir in sweet potatoes, carrots, galic, chopped ginger, chicken broth. cover, boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Transfer to food processor, puree until smooth.
Stir in the lime juice, and salt.
Makes 10 cups.
Each serving has 127 cal.... 4 g fat, 3 g protein, 21 g carb.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together well. Spread 1/2 mixture into greased and floured 9 X 13 pan. Crumble 1/2 of strudel onto mixture. Cover with remaining batter and top with rest of strudel. Bake at 375° for
25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork fried rice(makes 4 servings)
directions: In skillet or wok, over medium-high heat, cook rice in oil until golden brown, about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pork or ham and eggs.
Cook and stir until eggs are set.
Stir in scallions, steak sauce and soy sauce just until blended and heated through.
To serve, garnish with scallions.

title: cinnamon jello salad
directions: Melt candies in 1 cup boiling water (microwave or double boiler).
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add candy mix. Add applesauce.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Soak slices of bread in milk and add to squash.
Stir in eggs and cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: mexican 3-bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Chill and serve.

title: jan's kabobs
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients and marinate beef for at least 3 hours. If using wood skewers, soak in water for 15 minutes before preparing kabobs. Grill 4 to 6-inches from coals for 8 to 10 minutes, turning twice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar and cream thoroughly.
Add egg.
Sift flour and soda together and work into creamed mixture.
Form into balls and flatten out on a baking sheet with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.
I double this recipe.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt margarine/butter and chocolate chips according to directions on chocolate package.
Allow to cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Divide into two or three portions and place each portion on a piece of tinfoil.
Form each portion into a "log."
Sprinkle top of log with coconut.
Close tinfoil around log and place in refrigerator or freezer.
When ready to serve, slice the log.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut bread into small pieces; add all the ingredients, except for the sugar.
Mix everything in a bowl, making it into a batter.
Take the sugar and heat in pan, stirring constantly to create caramel.
Add the caramel into an oven tray and add the batter.
Cook in oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
When done, let it cool and serve.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup cheese for topping. Mix Veg-All, mayonnaise, 1 cup grated cheese, chestnuts and onion. Place in casserole dish. Mix crackers with butter and place on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Add remaining cheese the last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and boil about 15 minutes; drain. Make a white sauce by melting butter and stirring in flour, slowly adding half and half and salt and pepper.
Place onions in 2-quart casserole; top with cheese, then pour white sauce over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak 8 hours.
Drain.
Cover beans with water and add salt; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 2 hours; drain if necessary.
Place beans in a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish; add salt pork and onion.
Combine molasses, ketchup, mustard, pepper and 2 cups hot water; pour over beans. Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours, stirring once.

title: beef bourginoine
directions: Trim away any fat.
Cut meat into cubes.
Salt & pepper beef. Brown meat in bacon grease.
Drain off fat.
Add crumbled bacon, broth, 1 cup water, garlic, and bay leaf.
Simmer in covered pot. Stir; add onions, carrots, mushrooms.
Remove bay leaf.
Thicken 1/4 cup water and flour.

title: big d cake
directions: Place flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Place butter, cocoa, oil and water in a 2-quart saucepan and bring to boil. Pour hot liquid over dry and mix.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake in an 11 x 16-inch pan for 20 minutes at 400°. Five minutes before cake is done, begin to prepare icing.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in pan until it turns golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool. Pour melted Hershey chocolate bars over top.
Sprinkle with nuts. Freeze until top gets hard.
Break and eat.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 4 (1 pound) coffee cans sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: turkey chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, in margarine, saute onion and celery in margarine until tender-crisp.
Add broth, potatoes, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in turkey.
In a medium bowl, combine cornstarch and milk.
Stir in soup and cook until thickened.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: bite size pieces cooked Shady Brook Farms

title: italian bread
directions: Cut French bread in half lengthwise.
Spread sauce out over bread.
Fry hamburger, onion and mushrooms.
Drain.
Spoon out on top of sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add cheese.
Cook 10 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: just good fruit punch
directions: Make a syrup by boiling water and sugar in large saucepan; add remaining ingredients except carbonated beverage.
Mix well.
Pour into freezer container and freeze.
Before serving, allow to thaw to a slushy state.
Add chilled carbonated beverage.
Yield:
50 to 60 servings.

title: lemon-raspberry muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients; add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Place paper baking cups in muffin pan and coat with cooking spray.
Spoon batter into paper cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes at 425°. Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients into saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Cook 2 to 3 minutes after coming to a boil. Watch closely as this will boil over.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Grease and flour large Bundt pan.
Pour mixture into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until tests done.
When cool, remove from pan carefully.
Coat with warm Karo syrup.
Decorate with fruit, candied cherries, pineapple and nuts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When cool, ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off stem ends of peppers (cut up tops; add to ingredients).
Boil peppers 3 minutes in salt water, then drain.

title: cheese, bacon and eggs with rice
directions: Cut bacon up in 1-inch pieces.
Fry.
Leave drippings in pan. Scramble eggs in drippings.
Put cooked rice in pan; stir together.
After everything is combined, sprinkle cheese on top and cover.
Cut heat off.
Ready to serve.

title: cotton candy cookies
directions: Beat sugar replacement, orange oil and rind into the stiff egg whites.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325°F (165°C) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: banana nut pound cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Check with a toothpick.

title: company carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook carrots in boiling water until fork-tender.
Reserve 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Cut carrots in narrow strips.
Arrange in 9-inch square baking dish.

title: taco dip
directions: Pour salsa over top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Microwave for 10 minutes on High. Serve with chips.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat pineapple and pudding for 2 minutes. Mix in sour cream. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Serve with a dash of whipped cream.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix 1 envelope Knox unflavored gelatine, sugar and salt.
Add 1 1/2 cups very hot water and stir until gelatine is thoroughly dissolved.
Add vinegar or lemon juice; chill to unbeaten egg white consistency.
Fold in diced tart apples, diced celery and chopped pecans.
Turn into a 4-cup mold or individual molds. Chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens and serve with salad dressing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan brownies
directions: Melt butter, sugar, cocoa and vanilla. Mix in eggs to blend. Add 1/2 flour until blended. Stir in 1/2 cup pecans. Bake 25 minutes at 350° in greased and floured pan. Cool 30 minutes in pan. Turn out and cool completely. Cut into squares.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortenings;
beat until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat.
Add flavors; alternate milk and flour.
Beat after each addition.
Fold in coconut,
pecans
and
cherries. Bake
in
prepared Bundt pan at 325° to 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sam's easy chilli
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon.
Break biscuit dough in pieces and drop into bowl with sugar mixture.
Toss to coat dough.
Melt butter and pour over coated biscuit dough pieces. Transfer to a 12-cup Bundt cake pan, pouring any excess liquid over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cape cod chicken
directions: Mix rice, bouillon and seasonings. Sprinkle over bottom of buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up, on top of rice with larger pieces on outer edge.
In a small pan, heat the cranberry sauce, butter, lemon juice and soy sauce. Bring almost to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour cranberry mixture over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Uncover. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: speedy pie
directions: Melt margarine in deep dish.
Combine other ingredients except peaches,
pour
over
butter
and top with peaches.
If peaches are unsweetened, add sugar
to taste.
Bake 40 minutes at
350°, the crust rises to top.
Serve
hot
or
cold
with whipped cream or ice cream. Serves 6.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes in a preheated oven at 450°.
Turn oven down to 350°.
Bake 40 minutes or until done.
Use knife test.
Cool.
This pie is like a pumpkin pie.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix everything except for 3/4 cup of the Ritz crackers. Sprinkle them on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts in lemon sauce
directions: Cook sprouts according to directions, omitting salt.
Drain. Place them in a shallow 2-quart casserole; keep warm.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Heat tomato soup and add to gelatin.
Add cream cheese.
Stir well to blend.
Place in milk cartons to congeal.
Place on Ritz crackers to serve.
Garnish with olive and parsley.

title: my old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Beat in flour. Do not overbeat.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine mixture; spread on ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash celery; destring each piece. Cut into 2-inch pieces. Fill each rib with mixture of nuts, cream cheese and mayonnaise.

title: crispy oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray rack set in shallow baking pan with cooking spray.
In shallow dish, stir mustard, yogurt and vinegar to blend.
In second dish combine potato granules, Parmesan and paprika.
Dip chicken breasts first into mustard mixture, then into potato mixture to coat on both sides.
Arrange breasts on prepared rack in baking pan.
Bake about 20 minutes until chicken is cooked through and coating is lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients in 2-quart saucepan.
Add water; mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.

title: chuck roast
directions: Trim excess fat off roast.
Rub meat on both sides with the soup mix.
Line a roasting pan with enough heavy duty foil to make a tent.
Place meat in pan and fold foil over, securing all edges to prevent steam from escaping.
Place in oven and roast for about 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Leftovers may be used for sandwiches or soup.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in a small amount of hot oil.
Drain well; add chopped chilies, soups, enchilada sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook until well mixed.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain and add Ragu sauce.
Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Put a layer of meat and sauce mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; top with 3 noodles, then cheeses.
Repeat meat and sauce mixture, 3 noodles, then cheeses until all are used.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Chop tomato and set aside.
Cut avocados in half, remove seed and peel.
In a bowl, mash avocado with lemon juice.
Stir in salt, onion, garlic and picante sauce.
Spoon guacamole into a serving bowl. Garnish with tomatoes.
Serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: kale soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain and rinse.
Put into a large pot with broth, beef, linguica, chourico, onion, salt and pepper. Bring to boil; reduce heat to simmer.
After 30 minutes remove sausages and continue cooking until beans and meat are tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Remove meat.
(At this point I refrigerate overnight; remove fat before continuing.)
Add kale and potatoes. Simmer for 2 hours.
Cut meat and sausage into small pieces and return to soup.
For best flavor, let soup stand in refrigerator overnight before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 gallons.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Add lemonade concentrate, cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk to a blender.
Whirl until smooth and creamy.
I use hand mixer.
Scrape mixture into bowl.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Dip chicken wings into melted margarine; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle hot sauce evenly on top.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine.
