Roll out in balls and pat on ungreased cookie sheet. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar and blend until creamy. Blend in egg, peanut butter, vanilla, salt and soda.
Sift flour before measuring, roll dough into small ball and press with fork on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Add salt, garlic and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles as directed on carton.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour 1/3 of the meat sauce.
Cover with strips of lasagne, then 1/3 of Mozzarella and cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Top with
Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with a mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
In skillet, brown on both sides in hot shortening.
Place in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, 3/4 cup water, ginger and rosemary; pour over chops.
Sprinkle with half the onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining onions and continue baking 10 minutes.
Remove meat to platter. Blend sour cream into soup mixture; heat.
Serve with meat.

title: apricot bundt cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil	and
eggs
well.
Add baby food, flour, cinnamon and pecans.
Bake	in
greased
and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes a 300°.
Let stand 15 minutes before removing.
This cake will stay moist if tightly covered.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix shortening and margarine; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture; stir in vanilla.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, salt, pepper, 1/2 cup margarine and haddock or pollock in water until potatoes and fish are nearly done.
Then add milk and 1/4 cup margarine.
Simmer until done.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together until it starts to thicken. Add sour cream and a little less than half a container of Cool Whip (use rest for topping).
Make layers; start with vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Repeat and then top with remaining Cool Whip.
Makes large quantity.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chili supreme
directions: Combine cooked beans and tomatoes and simmer for 5 minutes. Saute green peppers in salad oil for 5 minutes.
Add onions; cook until tender, stirring often.
Add garlic and parsley; melt butter and saute meat for 15 minutes.
Add meat to onion mixture; stir in chili powder and cook 10 minutes.
Add this to beans and then add spices.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Skim fat off top.
Flavor will improve if set in refrigerator overnight.
May be frozen indefinitely.

title: crunchy tuna luncheon
directions: Drain tuna, pineapple and oranges.
Mix tuna with mayonnaise. Add fruit and chill in refrigerator.
Before serving, toss in noodles.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: creamy cheese sauce
directions: Melt cheese in milk over low heat, stirring constantly.
This sauce is to pour over Tuna Croquettes recipe.

title: old south corn patties
directions: In blender or food processor, combine corn and water.
Process but do not puree.
Add flour and eggs.
Process briefly. Transfer mixture to a bowl. Add all remaining ingredients except oil, mixing well.
Heat oil about 1/2 to 1-inch deep in skillet. Depending on size wanted, drop 1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture into heated oil, leaving space between patties.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden.
Drain patties on paper towels. Keep warm until all patties are fried.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Cut each tomato in 6 pieces, place in saucepan and cook until done.
Mash up.
Break up your bread in small pieces and add to tomatoes.
Stir (should be pudding consistency; add a little tomato juice if necessary).
Add butter, sugar, salt and pepper. Top with fresh dried parsley.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix ground chuck, 1/2 cup cheese, bread crumbs, milk and garlic salt.
Press into a 9-inch pan.
Cover with tomato sauce and sprinkle with oregano.
Spread mushrooms over top and add remaining grated cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Cut and serve in wedges.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stir and roll pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Measure flour, baking powder, salt, milk and 1/4 cup salad oil into bowl.
Stir vigorously until mixture leaves side of bowl.
Gather dough together and press into ball. Knead dough 10 times to make smooth.
Divide the dough in half.

title: chili
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: beef and noodle bake(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Dry fry the minced beef in a nonstick pan until browned.
Add the vegetables and stock cube; bring to the boil. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into an ovenproof dish.

title: special zucchini bread
directions: Remove seeds from raw zucchini and grate.
Mix eggs, oil, zucchini, sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder together.
Stir well.
Fold in vanilla and coconut/nut mixture.
Put into 2 loaf pans, greased, and bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool in pan tipped on side.
After 15 to 20 minutes, pop out of pans and continue cooling.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar and salt until fluffy.
Dip bread into egg mixture and arrange on buttered baking sheets.
Bake about 8 minutes on each side until golden brown.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils, cover with cold water, soak overnight.
Add more water if necessary to make 8 cups.
Cook until lentils are soft.
Add seasonings and vegetables.
Bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Season to taste.
Remove bay leaf.

title: easy cheesy potato soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with 2 1/2 cups water in skillet. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order listed.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.
Yields 4 servings.

title: frittata hors d'oeuvres
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Mix with Ricotta, Parmesan, mushrooms, onion, oregano, salt and egg.
Lightly butter 24 (1-inch) muffin cups.
Place a slice of pepperoni in the bottom of each if you like.
Spoon cheese mixture into cups.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Add sugar to the juice and boil.
Remove and stir in jello.
Add Coke, fruits and nuts. Chill well.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain blueberries and pineapple (saving the juice).
In a saucepan, combine blueberries, 1/2 cup sugar, water and lemon juice; bring to a boil.
Combine juice and enough water to make 3 cups; bring to a boil.
Pour in a bowl over the gelatin, stirring until all is dissolved.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Congeal.

title: granny thornhill's million dollar pie
directions: Combine above ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: shrimp platter
directions: Mix the Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and garlic together; combine with cream cheese.
Cover bottom of platter with thin layer.
Shake cocktail sauce on top.
Sprinkle shrimp on top. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread on top.

title: cola chicken
directions: Combine cola and ketchup in skillet.
Place chicken in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix and form into 4 loaves.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
Unwrap and place on cookie sheet or broiler pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool and slice thinly.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
In a large bowl, combine eggs and water.
Add remaining ingredients. By hand, stir until combined.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes until done.
Cool 30 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove from pan. Cool completely.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine liquid ingredients and sugar.
Measure dry ingredients together.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured 1-quart baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Combine flour and sugar. In
separate
bowl,
combine eggs and butter.
Stir in flour and sugar mixture.
Stir in salt, corn syrup and pecans. Pour
into pastry
lined pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for
10 minutes.
Turn temperature to 350° and continue baking for
50 more minutes.
Can be served warm or cool topped with whipped cream.

title: slaw
directions: Let the vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and salt come to a boil. Remove from heat and
cool.
Chop or shred the cabbage, pepper, onion and radishes.
Pour
the
cooled
liquid mixture over this and refrigerate.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish. Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry meat, garlic, salt and pepper until meat is brown.
Drain. Add rest of ingredients except cheese and simmer for 30 minutes. Cook noodles.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into large rectangular pan. Layer noodles and cheese on top, repeating twice.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: raisin banana bread
directions: Beat together butter, sugar and 1 egg.
Add milk.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir into egg mixture just until moist.
Then blend in bananas, raisins and nuts.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: artichoke souffle
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender or food processor until smooth.
Pour into small souffle dishes (about 6 ounces each). Bake in oven at 375° for 20 minutes or until top is golden. Serve warm with Wheat Thins or Triscuit crackers.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa together.
Beat eggs with sugar and blend the chocolate mixture into eggs.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Add nuts and bake 30 minutes at 350° in sheath cake pan. Spread hot cake with marshmallow cream.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Carefully clean crab meat.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serve on crackers.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 9x9x2 inch baking pan with shortening. Melt the butter and chocolate in a large saucepan over low heat. Remove the saucepan from the heat. Stir in sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts. Add the eggs and beat well with an egg beater. Pour the batter into the baking pan. Bake for 30 minutes. Remove the pan from the oven and place it on a rack. When the brownies are cool, cut them into squares.

title: lemonade
directions: Put ham in lard can.
Cover with water.
Bring to a rolling boil; boil for 1 hour.
Wrap can in blankets for 12 hours.
Trim fat and rind; debone.
Put in baking pan and glaze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 package of crescent rolls.
Mix hamburger, salt and flour.
Add cooked broccoli.
Mix milk, cream cheese and egg.
Boil together until cheese is melted.
Add to hamburger mixture.
Pour over rolls in pan.
Cover mixture with the other package of crescent rolls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add juice from oranges.
Fold in sherbet, whipped cream and oranges.
Chill.

title: spinach salad
directions: Shake mustard, olive oil and vinegar in tightly covered container.
Divide into four parts and arrange on heat-proof dishes.
Top each with red pepper, carrots, tomatoes and nuts. Top with your favorite grated cheese and warm in 425° oven until cheese begins to melt.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs in a large bowl. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; blend.
Add butter, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake for 1 hour.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Two cups of strawberries, one cup of pineapple and three cups of sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Cook 20 minutes in the morning.

title: carrot nut cake
directions: In large bowl or electric mixer, cream butter and sugar.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon peel.
Beat eggs one at a time.
Stir in vanilla, carrots and walnuts.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with orange juice.
Turn into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven 60 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Turn out of pan and cool completely on wire rack. Spoon Orange Glaze over top, letting it run down sides of cake and decorate with freshly grated carrots.
Makes 16 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Use with sliced pineapple, strawberries, bananas, apples or any of your favorite fruits!

title: frozen strawberry preserves
directions: Stir crushed berries and sugar together.
Bring water and Sure-Jell to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly and add to mixture and stir 3 minutes.
Pour in jars; cover tightly, let sit out for 24 hours.
Then freeze.
Some sugar crystals may remain, don't worry about them.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: deviled egg sandwiches
directions: Chop eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Spread on your favorite bread.
Enjoy!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, cook 3 minutes
to
remove
raw
flour taste.
Heat milk in another pan. Add
milk
to
flour mixture and stir well, until almost boiling. Turn
down and simmer a few minutes.
Add pepper and Tabasco. Stir in cream.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Alternate layers of oysters and bread crumbs in a casserole. Cover with any remaining crumbs.
Combine liquid, salt and pepper. Pour over oysters and crumbs.
Cook in a moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: marinated steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Marinate in refrigerator all day or overnight (at least 10 hours).
Grill or broil.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line pan with wax paper.
Pour water over shortening; add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well (200 strokes).
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture; beat until smooth.
Turn into pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Done when it shrinks from side of pan.

title: chocolate scratch cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cocoa.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla; beat thoroughly. Sift flour and baking soda.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to sugar mixture.
Pour in well-greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) or layered pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix cereal, sugar, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
(I add a handful of raisins.)
Store in a big covered jar or Tupperware in the refrigerator.
Fill greased muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: rice ortega
directions: Brown beef with chilies; remove from pan.
Brown Rice-A-Roni with drippings.
Add 2 1/2 cups of water, seasoning packet and tomatoes.
Boil, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add meat.
In large casserole layer beef, rice mixture, sour cream and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pigeon peas and rice(west indian dish)
directions: *Purchase dried bag pigeon peas at most supermarkets and canned green pigeon peas at a Spanish-American Bodega store.

title: vegetable stix
directions: Mix corn meal and salt and pepper to taste; add flour.
Mix well.
Cut desired vegetables into 2 or 3-inch strips.
Roll vegetables into coating.
Fry in hot vegetable oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with your favorite salad dressing or ketchup.

title: eggless, butterless, milkless cake
directions: Dissolve soda in small amount of water.
Boil sugar, water, raisins, spices and shortening 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes in 300° oven.

title: pork and fried noodles oriental
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender; drain.
Rinse in cold water and drain again.
Set aside.

title: bouquet
directions: Some sauces and soups you would tie a sprig of each herb together and remove after cooking.

title: brown sugar cake icing
directions: Boil to soft ball stage.
Beat well and ice cake.
Nuts can be put on top if desired.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add eggs; beat well. Sift together flour, soda, cloves and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture alternately with the applesauce. Add raisins and walnuts. Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salami rolls
directions: Clean peppers; remove stems and seeds.
Spread cream cheese onto salami; put pepper in middle and roll up.
Put toothpick through to hold together.

title: sonny's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal which has been spun in blender (or use finely chopped oatmeal), salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together, then add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet. Make golf-ball sized cookies and place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 9 dozen cookies.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix vinegar and salad dressing.
Add gelatin to heated consomme.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in mold.
Chill until firm.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dice and place in a large bowl.

title: oven stew
directions: Place in heavy duty foil.
Divide stew meat, potatoes, onions, carrots and celery.
Season each serving and divide the can of tomatoes over each.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain
juice
from
fruit.
Combine juice with pudding. Stir until
mixed good. Add fruit; you can also add marshmallows, coconut and maraschino cherries.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Marinate beef in 1/3 of brandy and red wine for at least 1 hour.
Turn occasionally.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Place in mixing bowl with 1 cup sugar, evaporated milk, 2 cups milk, vanilla, egg yolks and melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour into a 10 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Remove and make meringue.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Cover pudding with meringue and bake for 3 or 4 minutes until golden.

title: apple rolls(quick, easy apple dumplings.)
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups sugar and water in a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan. Cook for 5 minutes.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Put first layer of cracker crumbs, second layer of corn and third layer of oysters, etc.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: raw veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on a cookie sheet, forming ridge around sides.
Bake according to package instructions.
Cool.

title: burnt sugar candy
directions: Combine 2 cups sugar, milk and butter in a heavy 3-quart saucepan; stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until butter melts.
Place remaining 1 cup sugar in a heavy skillet. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and syrup is light golden brown.
Gradually stir this into butter mixture.
Cook until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; let mixture cool.
Beat at high speed with electric mixer until mixture will hold its shape.
Shape candy into two 7 x 1 1/2-inch logs.
Roll in pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap; chill 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into slices.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: cheesecake
directions: Take first set of ingredients, stir together and press into cheesecake pan.
Blend together second set of ingredients.
Pour into crust and bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Then take third set of ingredients and mix together. Pour over cooled cheesecake and bake for 10 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool for 3 to 4 hours.

title: pineapple pie no bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into graham crust. Top with cool whip. Keep in refrigerator.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in water until dry, then cool.
Add flour and sugar mixed with salt, then add sweet milk and cook until thick. Add vanilla.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, milk, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add cheese, onion and spinach; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Serve immediately or freeze.
Cut into squares.
If frozen, heat on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Makes 24 squares.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend mayonnaise, ginger, vinegar and onion.
Shake in approximately 1 tablespoon of soy sauce to color beige and to taste.
Add a few shakes of Accent and a dash of pepper.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add cup of hot water and sugar. Stir and add pineapple and lemon juice; stir and chill partially firm.
Whip 2 envelopes of Dream Whip and fold into gelatin.
Break cake in small pieces; place foil wrap in pan, place one layer of cake and one layer of gelatin until gone.
Chill overnight.
Take out of pan and remove foil.
Whip 2 envelopes Dream Whip and frost outside of cake.
Cover with coconut and keep in refrigerator.

title: roasted potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter; stir in catsup, mustard, paprika and salt.
Cut each potato into 4 wedges; slash each wedge crosswise every 1/4-inch but not through skin.
Place potatoes on cookie sheet and brush with 1/3 of butter mixture.
Bake 35 minutes or until tender.
Brush occasionally during baking with butter mixture.
After last brushing, sprinkle with bread crumbs.

title: goulash
directions: Fry meat (seasoned).
Saute onions in oil.
Cook macaroni in salted water; drain.
Add all ingredients to meat and place in a baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion in skillet.
Drain grease off.
Add tomatoes and beans.
Combine salt, sugar, pepper, chili sauce and tomato juice.
Stir into meat mixture.
Add cooked and drained elbow macaroni and mix well.
Cook on high until boiling then turn down to simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: junk salad
directions: Mix pineapple with cherry pie filling, Cool Whip and pecans. Add sweetened condensed milk.
Stir well.
Refrigerate.
This keeps well for some time.
Very good.

title: no-cook barbecue sauce
directions: In bowl, stir all ingredients together.
Brush meats or poultry, turning often during last 20 minutes of grilling.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: overnight coffee cake(serves 24)
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, cream butter with sugars until smooth.
Add eggs and buttermilk and beat until slightly fluffy.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt and mix well.
Spread batter in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Cover pan and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, bake in preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes or until brown. Do not overbake.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 24 squares.

title: quick cheese danish
directions: Unroll 1 package rolls and lay flat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and egg yolk, beat well.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat well and pour over rolls.
Unroll other rolls and lay over mixture.
Beat egg white and water.
Brush evenly over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: funeral casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix soups and sour cream together.
Add chicken, water chestnuts and onions; mix well.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Stir crackers into butter and spread over casserole.
Sprinkle top with poppy seed. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour beef stew
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Add next 6 ingredients, 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is tender, about 2 hours.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until syrup reaches 270° or forms a brittle ball when dropped into cold water.
Add vanilla.
(If desired, a couple drops of food coloring may be added to syrup.
Divide syrup in separate bowls for each color.)
Pour syrup over popped corn; mix thoroughly to cover all kernels.
Grease hands with butter and shape into balls.
(If desired, 1 cup of unsalted roasted peanuts may be added to popped corn.)
Number will vary according to size of each ball.

title: royal chip
directions: In a big bowl, mix brown sugar, sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, salt and baking soda, then the chocolate chips and nuts (if wanted).
Place on a greased cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook slow 14 to 15 hours
in
crock-pot.
Freeze or use hot water bath to can.

title: cabbage soup
directions: One can of tomatoes may be substituted for 1 can Ro-Tel if like it spicy.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix well all ingredients except onions; coat onions and deep fry.

title: confetti dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with vegetables.

title: coconut pineapple pies
directions: Mix ingredients all together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes and turn temperature down to 350°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly brown and set.

title: carrots lyonnaise
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan.
Add carrots and onions.
Cover and simmer on low or medium-low heat for 15 to 20 minutes until carrots and onions are tender, but not mushy.
Add chicken stock mix, sugar and flour.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into bowl.
Chill.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Mix apple slices with both sugars, cinnamon and either flour or starch (this thickens your apples).
Put mixture into prepared pie shells.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually; add syrup, butter, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 380° for 1 hour.

title: flank steak
directions: Combine all
ingredients;
pour over steak.
Marinate 6 hours or more,
turning
once.
Place
4 to 5 inches away from coals 8 to 10 minutes; turn.
Do the same for other side.

title: red rice
directions: *Recommend Eckrich or Hillshire Farms.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Before baking, top with 3 cups Rice Krispies sauteed in 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kathy's jello
directions: In medium sized pan, add 2 1/2 cups water to the pudding mix and cherry jello. Pour over medium heat and stir constantly until thick. Remove from heat and let cool. Make Dream Whip according to directions and add to the cooled mixture. Stir until mixed. Refrigerate until set.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together cream cheese, butter, vanilla and cream or milk. Slowly add powdered sugar until correct consistency.

title: creamy broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Add soup, cream cheese, chives and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Stir in beans and corn chips.
Put in casserole dish.
Add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dawn's white chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven. Bring to boil; reduce heat to simmer. Simmer for 20 minutes. To serve, top with Monterey Jack cheese and sour cream. You can make it as hot as you want it by the salsa you use.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix together and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese in large bowl. Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple and add to ingredients. Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: mexican appetizer squares
directions: Sprinkle 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking dish with cornmeal.
Unroll dough; press into pan, sealing perforations.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Combine sour cream and seasoning mix.
Spread over crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken; bone and dice.
Saute onion in Pam spray. Prepare spaghetti according to instructions on package, using chicken broth.

title: beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large roaster.
Cook in oven at 250° for 4 hours.

title: brussels sprouts
directions: Heat butter in frying pan.
Add the celery, onion and cook slowly until they are yellow.
Blend in the flour, salt and pepper and add tomatoes.
Stir and cook until the mixture is thick.
Put the brussel sprouts into a greased baking dish and add the tomato mixture.
Sprinkle the crumbs over the top.
Bake 350° about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: teenagers party punch
directions: Chill lemon-lime beverage and fruit juice in advance.
At serving time combine pineapple, orange and cranberry juices in punch bowl.
Gently pour in lemon-lime.
Add scoops of sherbet and serve.
Yields 24 cups.

title: potted peaches
directions: Cook until most liquid is out about as you would with dried peaches.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix onion, all peppers and salt; let stand overnight.
Put spices in cloth and tie tightly.
Add to mixture and bring to a boil or until thickened, about 1 1/2 hours, stirring often. Remove spice bag.
Pour relish into hot, sterilized jars.
Fill to top and seal.

title: quick and easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add sugar, oil, salt and egg.
Stir to dissolve sugar and salt.
Stir in 1 cup flour until smooth.
Cover with cloth and place on rack over bowl of hot water; let rise 15 minutes.

title: sopapias
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Mix remaining ingredients and pour in yeast mixture, then work dough. Roll out dough and cut into 1 to 2-inch squares. Fry in pan filled with 1/2-inch oil or in the Fry Daddy until golden brown. Top with powdered sugar and honey.

title: spinach lasagna(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine spinach, cottage cheese, egg, parsley and garlic powder.
Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with 4 lasagna noodles.
Spread 1 cup sauce over noodles.
Layer with 1/3 cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle 1/3 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers twice.
Sprinkle evenly with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 25 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer. Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 8 servings.
Contains 250 calories per serving and 5 grams fat per serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoon on a greased pan.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Season chicken.
Brown chicken.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add water to which cornstarch has been added.
Cook 1 hour on low heat.

title: onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat; saute onions until clear and tender.
Butter a 2 quart (8 x 11 x 2-inch) casserole.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of cracker crumbs.
Add onions and soup in alternate layers to dish that is lined with the cracker crumbs.
When dish is full, cover the top with beaten eggs and pour milk over top. Sprinkle grated cheese and reserved cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until brown and bubbly.

title: hot beef spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk until creamy.
Add dried beef, onion, pepper and sour cream.
Put in an 8 inch pie pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: unbelieveables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients together in a bowl.
Drop small balls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down lightly with a fork.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes, then enjoy!

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Remove skin from chicken (if desired).
Melt margarine in oven in a rectangular 9x13 baking dish or pan.
Mix bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with mixture and place skin side down in pan (pan and margarine should be hot).
Bake uncovered 35 minutes, turn, bake about 15 minutes longer or until juice from chicken is no longer pink.

title: million dollar pickles
directions: Leave the cucumbers whole. Cover with cold water and salt and let stand 7 days, covered.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Pour boiling water over dates; allow to stand for 20 minutes.
Beat egg; add sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Beat well.
Strain water from dates into egg mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt into mixture of egg and water. Add chopped nuts, dates and vanilla.
Pour into bread pans; bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 16 (1/2-inch) slices.

title: fabulously fantasy fudge
directions: Heat chocolate and milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat; blend in vanilla and salt.
Spread in buttered 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Chill until firm, then cut.
Recipe can be doubled in 8-inch square pan.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat and add oats, butter, vanilla and salt. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan. Mix well and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and oats.
When slightly cool, drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Mix dry ingredients, then add rest of ingredients.
Pour into three greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done in middle.
Be sure layers are completely cooled before frosting.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Put a large pot of water on and bring to a boil.
Core, a little at a time, the cabbage and blanch just until leaves are fairly soft.
Do not overcook.
Continue to core and cook until all leaves are removed.
Let cool down.
In a bowl, take 8 cups of rice, onion, garlic, salt and pepper; mix well.

title: mott's "luscious layers" cake
directions: Just substitute an equal amount of Mott's natural applesauce for the oil in a recipe.
Mott's provides that needed moisture and texture with none of the fat, none of the cholesterol.

title: red plum cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, baby food, vanilla and food coloring in mixer bowl; mix until blended.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and salt; beat for 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts; pour batter into Bundt pan that
has been oiled and covered with sugar.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: vegetable medley(microwave)
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, part of cheese, sour cream, pepper and part of onions in 1-quart casserole. Cook, covered, on High for 8 minutes in microwave (turn dish halfway through).
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Cook, uncovered, on High 1 minute or until cheese melts.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Mix and set aside first 3 ingredients.
Boil together all other ingredients.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate.
Will be good for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Place sliced cabbage in a large pot; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Place sliced onions and diced potatoes on top of cabbage.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lay pork chops on top and then sprinkle again with salt and pepper.
Cook until done. Approximate cooking time is 1 hour.

title: mexican coffee balls
directions: Mix chocolate wafers with almonds, cocoa powder and sugar. Dissolve instant coffee in cup of coffee liqueur and stir into crumb mixture with corn syrup.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls and roll in cinnamon sugar.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Mix flour and sugar/sugar substitute. Add eggs, spices, milk and orange juice. Add nuts, butter and salt. Grate potatoes, 1 cup at a time. (I use food processor.) Add to mixture after each cup so they won't turn dark. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 2 hours. Serves 10. (If doubling or tripling this recipe, do not double or triple butter.)

title: pumpernickel bread
directions: Stir cold water into cornmeal until smooth.
Add boiling water, cooking and stirring constantly for two minutes.
Add salt and sugar.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add potatoes and caraway seed that is dissolved in the 1/4 cup water.
Add both rye and white flour. Mix and knead to a smooth, stiff dough using white flour on the board.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled. Shape into two loaves and place in greased pan.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
I like more caraway seed.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add eggs and rest of ingredients. Bake at least 15 minutes on lightly greased pans in 350° oven.

title: brownies(easy, moist and delicious)
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Don't beat.
Melt the margarine and chocolate together and mix in all the rest of the ingredients. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Test with a toothpick for doneness.

title: bobby knight cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs, water, cream of coconut and coconut. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After baking, while warm, put holes in cake.
Pour remaining cream of coconut. Let cool.
Add 1 cup coconut and Cool Whip, then ice. Refrigerate.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Core apples, but do not peel. Peel orange.
Grind them with cranberries.
Drain pineapple.
Add to rest.
Add sugar.
Add 2 cups boiling water to Jell-O, then add all together.
Refrigerate.

title: oreo delight
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Crunch up all cookies with a rolling pin.
Add cookies to butter and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1/2 cup for topping.
In large bowl, combine cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust. Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top and chill for 30 minutes.

title: quick biscuits(usa)
directions: Grease 12 cup muffin tin.
Mix biscuit mix and water just until moist (do not overmix).
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in hot oven at 425°.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oats together; let stand 20 minutes. Cream together the butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs. Add in the oat mixture.
Mix flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together; gradually add to mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick ham casserole
directions: Butter bottom of
cake
pan with butter.
Place chicken over bottom of
pan
(boneless
breasts
or
chopped
pieces). Cover chicken with sauerkraut, drained.
Cover sauerkraut with cheese. Pour Thousand
Island
salad dressing over entire top of casserole.
Cover with foil
and
bake 1/2 hour at 350° and then 15 minutes uncovered.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Brush cut sides of apple and pear with lemon juice.
Alternate the apple, pear and pineapple on four wooden skewers.
Brush with marmalade.
Broil alongside fish 4 inches from heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until heated through and slightly tender.
Turn once. Serves 3.

title: chicken and rice medley
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni mix as package directs, adding chicken with water and contents of seasoning packet.
Continue to cook as package directs, adding remaining ingredients during last 10 minutes of cooking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts. Shape into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot, very carefully.
I find they will shatter if handled the least bit roughly, either when rolling in sugar or trying to eat them!

title: butternut squash
directions: Wash off butternut squash.
Cut squash lengthwise; cut off seed pocket.
Cut into pieces (usually between 2 and 3 inches). Put butternut squash in baking dish.
Fill dish about 1/4 inch or a little bit more with water.
Cover butternut squash with foil in baking dish.
Cook butternut squash for 60 minutes at 400°. Remove butternut squash from baking dish and water as soon as possible.
Take butternut squash and slash the meat with dull knife.
Add the butter, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Serve at once. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: best texas corn bread
directions: Pour 1/2 of batter in greased skillet or pan.
Sprinkle cheese and chiles on top, covering with remaining batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken picata
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in skillet over medium heat.
When butter has melted, add chicken.
Brown on both sides.
Place chicken in small baking dish.
Melt remaining butter in skillet on low.
Add lemon juice, garlic and parsley. Pour over chicken.
Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: cranberry-orange glaze
directions: Blend orange juice and cornstarch in saucepan. Add cranberry juice cocktail, spices, red pepper seasoning and sugar. Stir until blended. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and a few drops of red food coloring.
Makes 3 cups.

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Mix
whipped
topping
and yogurt together.
Add fruit. Put in pie crust.	Freeze for 3 hours.
Thaw 15 minutes before serving.

title: taco casserole
directions: Saute onion. Brown beef in sauteed onion. Add crushed tomatoes, refried beans and taco seasoning. Sprinkle cheese on top. Cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Just before serving, sprinkle crushed taco chips on top, then add shredded lettuce. You can add chopped onion and tomatoes if you like.

title: beef barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together. Pour over sliced roast beef and heat. Makes great sandwiches.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toast sesame seed and almonds in a small amount of oil.
In a large bowl, add noodles, cabbage and green onions.
Add sesame seed and almonds.
In a jar, shake together the remaining ingredients.
Add to salad and toss.

title: gluten free sesame seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pan of water on bottom shelf. Line pans (4 1/2 x 8-inch and 3 1/2 x 6-inch) with waxed paper folded double and then greased.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup milk and place over low heat to melt gelatin.
Set aside.
Add 1 cup milk. Sift all ingredients, except seed, several times.
Add gelatin mix, oil and eggs.
Add seed.
Spread and flatten in pans to corners. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cook in salted water.
Mash.
Add other ingredients. Mix and let stand awhile. Then bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with cheese while hot.

title: kevin's mexican dip
directions: Brown beef, then add seasoning mix.
Stir in water to desired consistency (1/2 cup).
Let mixture simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Meanwhile spread cream cheese in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with meat mix with beans mixed in.
Top this layer with chopped green chilies.
Finish by adding both layers of cheeses.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is entirely melted and mixture is bubbly.
Garnish with sliced black olives.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: "miss leize's" ice cream custard
directions: Heat milk first; do not boil. Mix sugar, cornstarch and eggs, beating well. Add this mixture to heated milk and cook over medium-low heat until thickens, stirring constantly. Then add Carnation cream and mix well. If desired, add fruit (peaches, strawberries, pineapple, etc.).

title: stir-fry vegetable batter
directions: In bowl, stir together cornstarch, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add water and egg.
Stir until smooth.
Dip veggies into batter and carefully add to oil.
Deep fry in hot oil at 375°.
Stir batter occasionally.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, turning once until golden and crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and peppers together.
Heat together remaining ingredients and pour over cucumber mixture.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep for a long time.

title: easy and fast chicken pot pie
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper (can use Mrs. Dash flavoring).
Put in bottom of pie crust.
Good idea to put it in a pie pan first.
Unfold and place top shell on and press around the edge.
Cut a slit in top.
Bake at 350° (preheated) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Make sure top is golden.
Let stand 5 minutes before you cut and serve.

title: poulet margot
directions: Mix soups, rice, wine and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken and let stand 2 hours in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl.
Roll into small balls and chill for half an hour.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions sausage and celery in margarine.
Combine with crumbled bread, seasonings and eggs.
Add broth, stirring until all bread is moist and soft.
Check seasonings and adjust according to taste.
Stuff inside turkey or place in a greased 3 quart casserole and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in saucepan on low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted. Beat sugar into cream cheese (softened). Add remaining milk and chocolate mixture and beat until smooth. Fold in whipped topping and blend smoothly. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm (4 hours). Store any leftover in freezer.

title: canadian honey drops
directions: Mix all together; chill well.
Form into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix dressing together.
Add to noodles and refrigerate.

title: fool proof pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add vinegar to milk and combine at once with flour mixture. Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: dutch green beans
directions: Cook green beans if they are frozen, adding seasonings. Dissolve cornstarch in the water.
Add vinegar and brown sugar and bring to a boil.
When beans are tender, add sauce and simmer about 2 minutes.

title: maui pine cream pie
directions: Put milk, sugar, salt and drained pineapple in saucepan; let come to near boil.
Mix cornstarch and egg yolks together with 1 tablespoon water and add slowly to milk mixture, stirring constantly until thick, on low fire.
Add butter and vanilla and remove immediately from heat.
Cool about 1/2 hour in refrigerator.

title: special k cookies
directions: Cook the sugar and syrup until soft ball; remove from heat. Add the peanut butter and cereal.
Mix well and drop onto wax paper.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Preheat oven 350°.
Pour into a pan and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: yogurt shake(diabetic recipe)
directions: Place all ingredients, except yogurt, into medium sized bowl. Mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Place strawberry mixture and yogurt into blender and blend on high until smooth.
Serve cold.
Makes 4 servings.
Three-fourths cup equals 1 milk.

title: 4 minute sausage gravy(modern day s.o.s.)
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, heat butter on High for 45 seconds or until melted. Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually stir in milk. Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir every minute. Stir in crumbled sausage. Microwave 1 minute. Serve over toast or biscuits.

title: anise candy
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to a hardball stage (275-300°). Remove from heat and stir in anise oil and food coloring. Pour into a greased pan. When almost cool, mark into squares with a sharp knife. You can also pull this like taffy and cut. Use granite or glass utensils for cooking.

title: stuffed baked clams
directions: Saute onion and celery (and pepper) in butter.
Add sauce and bread crumbs.
Add liquid and add 1/2 cup water to moisten if necessary.
Stuff shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Grind or grate cheese and Spam.
Add to cooked hamburger, along with other ingredients.
Simmer (the longer, the better). Put on bun half and broil.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Mix soy sauce, garlic, olive oil and sherry together and marinate tenderloin for several hours or overnight, turning several times.
When ready to cook, roast on rack in 425° oven for 28 to 30 minutes.
Baste with marinade from time to time.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in a small amount of water for about 5 minutes; add the sugar and butter.
Thicken the flour in a small amount of water mixed into a paste and add to raisins.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Mix
sugar,
water
and Kool-Aid.
Just before serving, add 7-Up and lime sherbet.
Makes 25 servings.
May be doubled for extra guests.
Great for Christmas parties.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt and pour over cereal in a large bowl.
Put 1 cup powdered sugar in a large brown bag; add cereal.
Add another cup of sugar; shake sack.
Pour out on wax paper to dry.

title: oriental salad
directions: Cook bean sprouts in small amount of salted water for about 3 minutes, just until tender-crisp.
Drain and cool.
Combine first 8 ingredients and chill thoroughly.
Add salt,
pepper and lemon juice.
Add dressing and toss lightly.
Sprinkle with soy sauce, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: fantastic fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges, pineapple and strawberries.
In a mixing bowl, combine oranges, pineapple, strawberries, peach pie filling, apricot pie filling and bananas.
Gently mix together.
Place in a beautiful crystal bowl for serving.
This is a wonderful fruit salad for special holiday dinners.
Serves 16.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: In a food processor, combine garlic, celery salt, pepper and salt.
In a small bowl, combine vinegar, mayonnaise, buttermilk and parsley.
Blend with garlic mixture; stir well.
Makes 1 quart.

title: dump cake
directions: In a square baking dish, dump pie filling, then cake mix. Melt butter and pour over the cake mix. Make sure that butter is even. Bake at 375° or 400° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cake will brown.

title: seafood spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, garlic and parsley in butter until tender.
Drain clams and shrimp, reserving liquid so you have enough for 1 cup, or add water to make 1 cup.
Combine cornstarch and liquid, stirring until blended.
Add to butter and onion mixture and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in clams and shrimp; heat to serving temperature.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Toss hot spaghetti with small amount of butter and Parmesan cheese (use additional cheese, if desired).

title: neopolitan ziti
directions: Bake or pan-fry Italian link sausages until fully cooked; drain, then cool sufficiently to be able to cut them.
Core and clean green bell peppers of seeds and membranes and cut into strips.
Cut the sausages in half lengthwise, then cut the split sausages into 1/2-inch slices.
Result will be semi-circles of sausage.
Saute green bell pepper slices in olive oil over moderate heat only until their crispness is lost, but peppers are not soft. Yields 4 servings.
May be increased proportionately.

title: cheesy vegie soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook onion in hot margarine or butter until tender, but not brown.
Add corn, broccoli, carrot, (tuna) and water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, cheeses and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese is melted and soup is heated through.
Serves 4 for dinner or makes 8 side dishes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients well and store in an airtight container. Add 2 to 3 heaping tablespoonfuls (or to taste) to a cup of hot water and stir well.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Boil until done and cut in 1-inch chunks. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).
Drizzle large bottle Hidden Valley Ranch dressing over top.
Sprinkle 2 cups grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Place all items in large soup pot and simmer for 1 hour. Granular chicken bouillon can be substituted for cubes or you can use can of chicken stock and eliminate the hot water.

title: aunt mary's punch
directions: Add all the ingredients in a large punch bowl.
You can float ice cubes in the punch with raspberries or strawberries frozen into them.
Lemon or lime slices also look nice as does daisies for a decorative note.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, water and nutmeg and boil 1 minute. Stir in butter. Peel and slice apples. Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Cut in lard with fork and add milk. Stir until moistened. Roll and cut in 6 squares. Place few apples on each square and sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Dot with butter. Seal edges. Place in oiled pan and pour syrup over dumplings. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except nuts and crackers or chips.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter or margarine (first four ingredients).
Mix until crumbly.
Press into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: black bean soup and pumpkin
directions: To prepare the beans:
Wash them in cold water, picking out any foreign matter.
In a large bowl or pot, cover the beans with cold water and soak overnight.
The following day, drain the beans.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place 6 slices of bread on the bottom of an extra large casserole pan.
Brown sausage and drain.
Spread half of sausage on bread.
Spread half of both cheeses over sausage.
Layer again. Mix egg, milk and salt; pour over layers.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: granny's strawberry sherbet
directions: Combine sugar and 1 cup water; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and dissolve gelatin in hot syrup.
Add 2 cups water and fruit juices.
Turn into freezing tray.
When partially frozen, turn into cold bowl and beat with a rotary egg beater until blended and fluffy.
Return to tray and continue freezing, stirring every 30 minutes until mixture holds its shape.
Then freeze until firm.
Freezing time: 5-6 hours.
Makes about 1 qt.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Pour in baking dish. Crush Ritz crackers; add butter.
Put on top of dish and bake 30 minutes.

title: cornmeal biscuits
directions: Combine
dry ingredients. Cut in shortening until about pea size.
Add	milk and stir until moist. Turn out on floured surface and knead about 20 times.
Pat to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit
cutter.
Bake
in lightly greased baking pan at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Place in bag and marinate 15 minutes.
Grill.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and add onion.
Mix together soups and enchilada sauce. In oblong pan, layer 1/2 of the meat, tortillas, soups and sauces and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together into ungreased 8-inch cake pan the first 5 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix together with fork.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: bean dip
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with refried beans.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning with just a little water. Simmer 5 minutes.
Layer meat mixture on top of beans, then spread sour cream.
Finish by covering top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first six ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on a rack in a baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: In a large bowl, crush biscuits.
Add boiling water, Crisco, salt, sugar and molasses.
Let cool.
Then add yeast dissolved in warm water and 6 cups flour.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down.
Put on board and divide into 2 loaves.
Knead a bit more and put in well-greased pans.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chopped butter in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Pour rice over butter and add soup.
Place chicken on top of rice; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Measure flour and sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine with first mixture along with sour cream.
Spread half of batter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
On top of this spread 1 can Thank You cherry pie filling, then spread remaining batter over this.

title: beef stew provencale
directions: Remove rind from salt pork; cut pork into 1/4-inch slices. Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
(For ease in cutting, partially freeze beef about 1 hour.)
Fry salt pork in Dutch oven over medium heat until crisp; remove with slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towels.
Cook and stir beef in hot fat until brown, about 15 minutes; drain fat.
Add wine, water, garlic, salt, thyme, rosemary, pepper and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir and cook for one minute .
Remove from microwave; add baking soda.
Stir rapidly.
Spoon out rapidly onto a greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the broccoli in enough boiling unsalted water to cover until just tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Rinse under cold running water; drain and set aside.
In another large saucepan, heat the olive oil over moderately low heat for 30 seconds; add the garlic and cook, uncovered, until golden, about 3 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, raisins and cayenne pepper and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add the pine nuts and simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: winter warmer
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients in 30 cup coffeepot basket.
Put other ingredients in coffeepot and perk.

title: brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; blend well with melted butter and vanilla.
Add eggs and nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300 degrees in a 9 x 13 inch greased pan.
Ice with Chocolate Brownie Frosting.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls using 1/3 cup measuring cup. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and freeze.
Place in plastic bag and store until ready for use.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
You may put a thick slice of tomato underneath before baking.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt and sift over fruit and nut mixture; mix well.
Mix sugar, vanilla and cinnamon, then add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each egg.
Mix batter with fruit and flour mixture.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix well chicken soup, mushroom soup, dry onion soup, rice and water in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake in 350° oven until chicken is brown (approximately 1 1/2 hours).

title: blueberry loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Add blueberries, egg, orange rind and orange juice to dry ingredients.
Mix until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: texas cake
directions: Melt margarine in 1 cup of water in saucepan.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in greased jelly roll pan.

title: turkey fillet
directions: Roll turkey slices in egg, salt and pepper.
Coat with flour. Brown in skillet with small amount of shortening.
Bake in layers, in greased square baking dish, of turkey, onion, soup and 1/4 cup water or milk.
Bake, covered, with lid or foil for 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange eggnog
directions: Mix everything in a bowl and beat for two minutes.
Pour into glasses and share.
Serves two.

title: diane's caesar salad
directions: In large bowl, mix garlic, salt, pepper, anchovies, lemon juice and egg.
Add olive oil and mix to combine.
Add lettuce and toss.
Add Parmesan cheese and croutons and toss again.
Serves 4.

title: grandma scott's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Top with meringue.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Melt 3 tbsp. butter in double boiler.
Blend in flour, pepper, paprika and salt.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Then add cheese, stir until melted.

title: cheddar potato slices
directions: In a bowl, combine soup, salt and pepper.
In greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half of mixture into a greased 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle about 3/4 of the cheese over this, saving the rest for topping.
Add remaining mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jeannie's casserole
directions: Saute celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into large casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna melt croustades
directions: With a fork, remove the soft crumbs from the rolls, leaving a 1/4-inch shell and reserve it for another use.
In a bowl, combine well the tuna, celery, scallions, 2/3 cup mayonnaise, mustard, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Brush the insides of the rolls with the remaining 1/3 cup mayonnaise; divide the tuna mixture among the rolls, mounding it slightly and top each with a slice of the Muenster.
Bake the croustades on a baking sheet in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until the filling is puffed slightly and the cheese is bubbly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in sifted dry ingredients; add nuts.
Bake in
two loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef and onions together.
Then add all other ingredients and let boil.
Then turn down to simmer.
Let simmer for 3 hours.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix well and spread over crust.
Then mix 2 small packages instant chocolate pudding with 3 cups cold milk.
Beat pudding until smooth and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread one small carton Cool Whip on top and sprinkle chopped pecans over Cool Whip.
Chill for 3 hours before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine milk, butter and bread cubes in greased dish.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat.
Beat eggs slightly, then add to bread mixture.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then test with knife to see if pudding is done.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream Crisco; add sugar and cream.
Add 3 eggs, beating after each egg.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately to egg mixture with milk.
Beat well and fold in berries.
Fill paper cups 2/3 full and sprinkle lightly with a little granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 24 to 30 muffins.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon slices into 1/3rds.
Wrap bacon around chestnuts. Secure with toothpicks.
Pour sauce over chestnuts and bake in 250° oven for 45 minutes, or until bacon is crisp.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt 1/2 of vanilla ice cream.
Fill pie shells half full of ice cream; freeze.
When frozen, drizzle caramel and chocolate fudge on pie.
Fill pie up to top with other half of melted ice cream; freeze.
Decorate with fudge and/or caramel as desired. You can also add chocolate chips, walnuts, peanuts, etc.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Heat 2nd pie shell just a few seconds in 350° oven.
Turn it out on top of pie.
Work edges together to seal.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour batter into an unbaked pie shell and bake until pie is brown.

title: light banana bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients; set aside.
In mixing bowl, beat together egg whites and sugar (this can be done by hand); add mashed banana.
Add oil and mix well.
Stir flour mixture into banana mixture.
Gently fold in currants.

title: coffee bars
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Add coffee; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake in 11 x 16-inch shallow pan (jelly roll pan) at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
While warm, glaze with icing made with 1 tablespoon hot coffee combined with 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut when cool.

title: plantation rice
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 1/2 hours.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Brown roast on both sides.
Place in crock-pot and pour dried onion soup over the roast.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Let cook until done. May add carrots and potatoes if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Mix together and serve.

title: puffins(for breakfast)
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Mix dry ingredients together in another bowl.
Add flour alternately with 1/2 cup milk.
Fill well-greased muffin pans full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Beat eggs and stir in oil and vanilla.
Blend in sugar; stir in dry ingredients and mix until well blended.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Blend cocoa, flour and sugar.
Add boiling water.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter and stir.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine pudding mix, cake mix, chocolate chips, milk and eggs in large bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes. Fold in nuts.

title: colonial pumpkin squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in pumpkin and eggs.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Spread in greased and floured pan.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 15-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Frost with cream cheese or buttercream frosting.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nutmeg and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Add eggs one at a time to mixture.
Pour mixture into pie shells and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Remove pies from oven and sprinkle with nutmeg and sugar.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 2 pies.

title: caramel pecan rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 5 tablespoons of oleo; stir in brown sugar, water and nuts.
Mix well.
Separate each can of rolls into 4 rectangles; seal perforations and spread with 3 tablespoons of softened butter.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and pepper together.
Add cheese, milk, soup and noodles.
Pour into casserole dish and crumble 1 or 2 slices of bread on top.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan; salt.
Lay chicken skin side up over rice.
Mix soup and water; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle soup mix over.
Bake covered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: south carolina angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, add sugar, cut in shortening, add buttermilk then add yeast.
Mix dough and place in icebox.
Take out as much as needed at a time.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add Doritos last and dressing last.

title: sour cream lemon glaze cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch layer pans. Combine in large bowl and mix at medium speed for 2 minutes the cake mix, water, sour cream and eggs.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Cake is done when toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely. Refrigerate for 1 hour (for ease in splitting layers).

title: pea and cheese salad
directions: Chill peas in their liquid and then drain.
Dice cheese small and combine with other ingredients.
Toss gently.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: sheepherder's hearty soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter and blend in flour.
Add water and milk.
Cook, stirring until thickened and smooth.
Add beans, corn (undrained), tomatoes and cheese.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Add hot pepper sauce, salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook only 1 bag of rice as directed. Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish including rice. Top with French fried onion rings. Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: all-time favorite potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: pear salad
directions: Place pears in a large bowl; pour jello over top.
Heat juice from pears and pour over pears and jello.
Mix well with hand mixer.

title: quiche elegant
directions: Brush inside of pie shell with small amount of beaten egg. Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 5 minutes.
Set pie shell aside.
Reduce oven temperature to 375 degrees.
Stir together cheese, chicken, mushrooms, chilies and pimento.
Pour into pie shell.
To the beaten eggs, add remaining ingredients.
Beat well until blended.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat the cream cheese and butter at low speed.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla, beating until creamy.

title: my own chili
directions: In large saucepan, fry hamburger, garlic and onion.
When browned, add tomato paste, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, bouillon cube, garlic salt, pepper and chili powder.
Stir and let simmer 30 minutes.
Add chili beans and simmer an additional 15 minutes until warmed through.

title: panama drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar; beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together. Blend into banana mixture.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon. Drop cookie dough from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until browned.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: family favorite potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice 1 1/2 inches thick.
Slice onion 1/4-inch thick.
Place in large saucepan and add salt, pepper and enough water to cover.
Cook on medium-high until potatoes are tender.
Drain off liquid.
Add Velveeta and sour cream until well blended.
Place mixture in large casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.
(Can also be heated in microwave or crock-pot.)

title: kasha varnishkas
directions: Heat broth to boiling in a deep pan.
Beat the egg lightly with a fork in a bowl.
Add the kasha to coat the kernels.

Put the kasha in the pan and heat on a medium flame, stirring the kasha until the egg has dried and the kernels are separate. Reduce heat to low and stir in broth and remaining ingredients. Cover pan and heat 8 to 11 minutes until all liquid is absorbed. Mix the kasha, bow ties and fried onions together and serve as a side dish.

title: irish tea biscuits
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add raisins, caraway seed and rind. Stir in the egg and buttermilk just to moisten.
Turn on a well floured surface and knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
With a biscuit cutter or inverted glass rim, cut out biscuits.

title: egg kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dry.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, stirring after each until all is used.
Add vanilla and beat.
Add vinegar and beat.
Add cream of tartar and beat.
Spoon mounds on cookie sheet and round out with a spoon.
Grease cookie sheet with Crisco and sprinkle cream of tartar over it.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: chive and cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Cut in 1/4 cup of butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly. Stir in cheese and chives.
Add milk, gradually, stirring just until moistened.
Shape into ball.

title: yummy cupcakes
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together and add pecans.
In separate bowl mix only until blended:
flour, sugar, eggs and water.
Do not beat!
Fold together and fill cupcake tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Need no icing.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
In a 7 x 11-inch casserole dish, put rice in first.
Add beef consomme and water.
Add browned sausage. On top of that, add mushrooms and the slivered almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour, or until brown.

title: peach jam
directions: Mix fully ripe, mashed peaches with sugar and lemon juice. Let stand for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1/2 bottle liquid pectin; stir for 2 minutes.
Add to peach-sugar mixture. Mix well; pour into clean jars.
Cover with lids.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour, then refrigerate.
Jam must be stored in refrigerator or freezer.
Will keep 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator or 6 months in freezer.

title: easy oven stew
directions: In Dutch oven, combine meat, potatoes, onion, carrot and celery.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over meat and potatoes.
Mix well.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Serves 4.

title: garlic vegetables(low calorie)
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook cauliflower and garlic in 1 Tbsp. hot butter for 1 minute. Add white wine and salt, bring to boil. Cover and Simmer for 3 minutes. Stir in broccoli, cover and cook 3 minutes or until crisp or tender. Stir in carrots and remaining 1 Tbsp. butter. Cook until butter is melted.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Seal chicken in foil, place in shallow pan and bake at 350° until done.
Unwrap chicken, cut up and place back in pan with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until very bubbly. Serves 12.

title: herbed potatoes(lori)
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, layer potatoes and onions; sprinkle Mrs. Dash.
Continue until all are used.
Combine butter and water and pour over potatoes.
Cover bowl with waxed paper and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Adjust time to 15 minutes if a larger amount of potatoes is used.

title: johanne day's hermits
directions: Mix milk and molasses together.
Mix all dry ingredients with oil.
In a large mixing bowl, add the two mixtures, alternately. Bake on cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green bean and sausage casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onions.
Pour into large casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with onions and bake until onions are crisp.
Add fruit salad and rolls for complete meal.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Put corn puff curls in roaster pan.
Set aside.
Mix the brown sugar, margarine and Karo syrup in pan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda (will bubble up).
Pour mixture over corn puff curls and stir.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: cheese dough
directions: Cream margarine and mix with grated cheese.
Add salt, pepper and flour.
Mix by hand.
Can roll dough around bits of meat. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Check after 8 minutes.
(Can freeze ahead.)

title: pistachio surprise
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding mix together.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Stir all together.
Chill and serve cold as salad or dessert.

title: granola snack mix
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
In a large bowl, combine the oats, walnuts, coconut, sunflower seeds and pie spice; mix well.
Pour the syrup over the oat mixture, stirring well.
Spread the mixture in a single layer on a lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, then stir in rhubarb and nuts, then combine last 4 ingredients.
Stir this into rhubarb until blended.
Spoon into muffin cups, 2/3 full.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix together water, vinegar and oil; shake well with garlic, peppercorns, thyme, oregano and salt.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and refrigerate.
Also good sliced in salads.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as per directions on box.
Strain well.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Combine with broccoli.
Pour into casserole.
Top with butter and crackers.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Serves 15.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add egg and melted oleo.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Mix in liquid and egg; mix well. Keep in refrigerator until ready to use.
Put in muffin cups sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Do not let rise.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken and set aside to cool.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
While sauteeing, add wine to the pan.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Melt remaining butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Stir in broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in mushrooms including liquid from pan.
Cut chicken from bones and divide shredded meat evenly into two 2-quart casseroles.
Divide spaghetti in half and put on top of chicken. Pour sauce over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly and lightly browned (about 30 minutes). Makes 12 servings.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Place margarine, Crisco and sugar in bowl.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, alternately with flour.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into well greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: tapioca fluff(microwave)
directions: Combine egg yolks, 3 tablespoons sugar, salt, milk and tapioca in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Let stand 3 minutes to soften tapioca. Place in oven.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes on "8" or until mixture thickens, stirring twice.
Beat egg white until foamy in 2-quart bowl.
Gradually beat in 2 tablespoons sugar, continue beating to form soft peaks.
Fold in tapioca carefully but thoroughly.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
