Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla together.
Mix well.
Add potato chips and stir in flour.
Form small balls from mixture and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Press balls flat with the bottom of a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour mix into greased 10-inch pan with removable bottom.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Cool 1 hour.
Decorate with nuts and oranges.

title: corn chip pie - casserole
directions: Crush 2 cups of corn chips (enough to cover pan bottom) and spread in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Season to taste with chili powder or Creole seasoning.
Sprinkle part of the chopped onion and one cup of shredded cheese over the chips.
Spread the chili over the onion, cheese and chips.
Top with remaining chips, onion and cheese.
Add more seasoning, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Tastes even better warmed up the next day.

title: mom's potatoes
directions: Melt margarine, onion, and salt together.
Mix with cheese, sour cream, and soup.
Mix hashbrowns
into mixture and add ham chunks.
Put in 9 x 11 inch baking pan and put chips or corn flakes on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb-raisin pie
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Turn into 9-inch pastry shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Brush top with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Cover pastry edges with foil to prevent overbrowning.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute and stir zucchini, onion and butter or margarine for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add salt, pepper, basil, garlic powder, parsley and oregano.
In a bowl, beat eggs and add Mozzarella cheese.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Press 1 package crescent rolls into a pan and spread with mustard.
Pour zucchini mixture into pan and bake. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and serve.
I bake in a 9 or 10-inch glass pie plate.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in an airtight container.
Add 3 tablespoons mix to 1 cup hot water.
Stir to dissolve.
May top with marshmallow.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding chicken last.
Pour into large casserole dish and bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and continue baking for 15 minutes.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Beat 2 eggs and pinch of salt until foamy.
Beat in sugar, hot water, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Fold in sour cherries. Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Layer remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Grind the first four ingredients through a medium blade grinder.
Add salt and sugar.
Use Miracle Whip salad dressing to moisten to your liking; not too runny.

title: lyonnaise potatoes
directions: In hot butter in large, heavy skillet, saute potato and onion slices, turning frequently, until golden brown and tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: autumn apple bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add alternately with the grated apple to egg mixture.
Stir in lemon peel and walnuts (batter will be stiff).
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan (8 x 5 x 2-inch) in moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Do not slice until cold.

title: grandma's bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water 24 hours.
Rinse well.
Soak 3 hours more in clear cold water.
Change water every hour.
Drain well.

title: barbecue venison
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Put aluminum foil in a 2-inch deep pan.
Put meat in pan.
Pour sauce over meat.
Bake in 375° oven until meat is done, about 2 1/2 hours, according to your oven (some ovens cook hotter) and also depends on tenderness of venison.

title: meat ball soup
directions: Cook vegetables in the water for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle garlic salt and pepper on ground beef; make beef into round balls.
Drop in soup.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: shipp's tabasco pickles
directions: Drain juice off pickles.
Put into container large enough to hold pickles and sugar.
Mix with hands until dissolved.
Add other ingredients and put back into gallon jar.
Put on lid.
Place in refrigerator for about 14 days, then enjoy.
They are worth waiting for.

title: merluza a la senorita (spanish)(baked hake with bananas)
directions: Have fish split.
Place in buttered flame-proof baking dish. Brush with a little oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Crumble bay leaves and sprinkle over.
Combine tomato puree with oil and stir in water and sugar.
Spread sauce around and along the center of the fish.
Peel and split bananas lengthwise and arrange around fish.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for about 30 minutes, basting with sauce occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: betty's corn pone pie
directions: Saute green pepper and onion with hamburger.
Add tomato sauce and pinto beans plus juice to hamburger mixture.
Mix corn bread mix as package directs.
Pour over hamburger mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: great vegetable soup
directions: Saute vegetables in skillet in 3 tbsp of butter until crisp tender.
When almost done, bring broth to a boil.
Add softened vegetables to boiling broth.
Simmer 15 minutes until tender.

title: peppermint brownies
directions: Make brownies according to the box.
Cool.
Melt peppermint patties in a small saucepan.
Frost the brownies with peppermint sauce.
Let sauce get hard, then cut into squares and enjoy.

title: date balls
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and dates in a saucepan. Mix well. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add pecans, cereal and coconut.
Mix well. Shape into small balls. Roll in powdered sugar.
Put margarine in palms of hands when making balls; will be sticky.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and chop.
Oil 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with tortilla shells.
Blend soups and Ro-Tel.
Pour 1/2 over shells.
Spread 1/2 of chicken.
Spread 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Save liquid.
Pour milk over bread crumbs and let stand 5 minutes.
Add salmon, liquid, minced onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven or until firm.
Unmold and serve. Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine together, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until creamy, then add egg yolks.
Add baking soda to buttermilk and add alternately with the flour.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into batter, adding vanilla and coconut at the same time.
Bake in three 8 or 9-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook noodles in broth until done. Saute onions in small amount of oil.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 1 large or 2 small casserole dishes.
Top with cheese, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: quick aspic salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. When slightly cooled, add lemon juice and stewed tomatoes.
Mix well together. (Using hands is a good way to mix.)
Put in molds or square pan.
When set, serve on lettuce leaves.

title: potato and sausage chowder
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in onion; cook on medium until tender (5 minutes).
Stir in flour until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in potatoes, milk, salt and pepper.
Cover; continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are fork-tender (25 to 30 minutes).
Stir in cheese and sausage.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted and sausage is heated through (2 to 3 minutes).

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix jello and hot water together.
Chill until jello mounds from a spoon.
Cream together sugar and cheese.
Whip the evaporated milk and add vanilla to milk.
Combine all together in mixing bowl and pour into chilled graham cracker crust.

title: cheese-stuffed meat loaf
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Mix
beef,
onion, egg, bread crumbs, salt,
pepper
and 1 can of tomato sauce.
Pat half of the mixture
into loaf pan, place cheese down center and cover with remaining
meat,
pressing	edges of meat together.
Top with the second
can of tomato sauce and bake 1 hour or until done.	Serves 6 to 8.

title: no-crust coconut pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 large or 2 small pies.
Don't overcook.
Remove from oven while still soft and shaky.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, and flour.
Slowly add mixture to warm milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thick in top of double boiler.
Add butter and vanilla beating well.
Spread meringue on top.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cake pan.
Mix butter, sugar and applesauce together.
Add flour, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Fold in nuts or raisins.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Combine onion and green pepper.
Stir together the rest of the ingredients and mix with carrots, green pepper and onion.
Cover and marinate.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
In a large bowl, mix potatoes, soup, Cheddar cheese and sour cream.
Add butter and onions and mix well.

title: swiss ham ring around
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix together parsley, onion, mustard, margarine and lemon juice.
Add Swiss cheese, broccoli and ham.
Set aside.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in muffin pan at 350° until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Mix shortening and sugar in a bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cloves and cinnamon.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean when stuck in middle.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: baked hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together hash browns, soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup melted butter.
Place in casserole dish. Mix corn flakes and 1/2 stick butter together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all thoroughly.
Put in a well-greased baking dish. Prepare 1 cup bread crumbs and 1/2 cup butter; brown slightly. Spread over casserole and top with sliced almonds.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mitsutaki
directions: Expand ingredients as your creativity desires.

title: linguini with white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil.
Drain clams and add to vegetables.
Continue to cook 10 minutes.
Add flour and stir well.
Add wine, spices and broth.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cheese.
Serve over linguini.

title: berry dessert
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13 pan, pat.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put all ingredients into food processor container, cover and process at blend until smooth. Chill before serving.
Yields 2 cups.
Serve with your favorite crackers.
Very delicious.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain fat.
Add mustard and catsup and stir good.
Add chicken gumbo soup and let heat.
Serve on buns.

title: peach bread
directions: Drain peaches, set aside syrup and chop peaches into fine pieces, then set aside. (If using fresh peaches, peel and chop fine.)

title: diet workshop vegetable soup
directions: Simmer first 6 ingredients together for 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer all together for about 30 minutes longer.
Separate cauliflower so it falls apart and looks like ice granules.

title: reuben appetizers
directions: Place thin sliced cheese on bread.
Top with 2 teaspoons sauerkraut; add turkey or corned beef, then scant teaspoon of dressing.
May be refrigerated up to 2 hours.
Heat in oven. Garnish with pickle.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion; drain. Mix with all other ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: gingered vegetables
directions: In 10-inch skillet or wok over high heat, in hot oil, stir-fry carrots, celery, red pepper and onion 3 minutes.
Add broccoli, snow peas, garlic and ginger.
Sprinkle cornstarch over vegetables. Stir in broth; cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring often.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serve with soy sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 cups or 4 servings.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Butter an 8 or 9-inch metal cake pan.
Set aside.
In a glass bowl, microwave the first two ingredients on High for 4 minutes. Add nuts and microwave on High for an additional 3 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla last and microwave on High for 2 more minutes.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool.
Loosen carefully when cool and candy can be removed in one round piece.
Wrap in colored Saran Wrap or cellophane wrap.
Tie with ribbon to give as gift.
Do not use glass pan, as glass will not give when candy has cooled.

title: pineappleade
directions: Combine pineapple juice and lemonade.
Just before serving, add lemon-lime soda.
Serve over ice in tall glasses.
Makes 9 servings (8 ounces each).

title: shortcut lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in oil.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce, sauce mix and vegetable juice.
Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Cover the bottom of an oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with a thin layer of meat sauce.
Add a layer each of uncooked noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with meat sauce. Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; let stand 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and chopped parsley.
Cut in squares to serve.
Serves 12.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In medium
bowl, combine oats, coconut and walnuts; set aside. In
quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa. Cook
over	medium	heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to
a
full
boil,
3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, coconut and walnut mixture.
Quickly drop mixture	 by rounded
teaspoonfuls
onto
waxed	paper.	Cool completely. Store in refrigerator.

title: good barbecue
directions: Simmer all in a heavy pan.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Make tea and add sugar to dissolve.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Freeze.
Place slush in glass to 1/2 mark, then add club soda or 7-Up when ready to serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in desired pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fried corn bread
directions: Mix
meal,
flour, baking powder and salt.
Add egg and milk to	make
a stiff batter.
Drop by spoonful into hot fat. Fry until brown on both sides.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
In separate bowl, mix oil, vanilla, cold water and vinegar. Gradually combine dry and liquid mixtures.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix margarine and eggs, then mix in sugar.
Add bananas and all remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Check center with toothpick after 50 minutes.

title: ruth's fluffy dessert
directions: Mix dry jello powder with cottage cheese.
Add drained mandarin oranges.
Mix well.
Add drained crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip, mixing well.
Refrigerate.

title: old fashioned apple butter
directions: Wash, peel and quarter apples.
Bring apples and cider to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes. Puree apple mixture in blender.
Add sugar and spices, mixing well. Pour puree into a shallow baking pan and bake at 300° for 2 hours or until thick to hold its shape.
Pour into hot sterile jars and seal.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: five minute corn soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the egg, in a saucepan.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat to simmer.
(You may thicken with cornstarch, if you so desire.)
Pour egg slowly into the bubbly soup.
Continue to stir.
Season to taste (really not necessary). Garnish with chopped green onions.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix applesauce and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add bananas, flour, soda, salt and nuts (optional).
Mix. Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Fold ham around cheese slices, then chicken around ham.
Hold in place with toothpicks.
Melt butter in pie plate.
Mix bread crumbs, salt and paprika in a second pie plate.
Roll stuffed chicken breast first in butter, then crumb mixture.
Coat well, place a single layer in a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots in salted water (just until tender).
Drain well and add sour cream and soup.
Mix dressing with butter (only) no liquid.
Alternate vegetables with buttered dressing crumbs.
End with crumbs on top.
Add grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Warm cheese and soup in saucepan until well blended.
Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add gelatin, softened, to tomato/cheese mix. Remove pan from heat.
Add all other ingredients and mix gently. Pour into mold.
Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.

title: easy strawberry and pineapple angel food dessert
directions: With 2 plates, divide angel food cake into 2 horizontal equal pieces.
Put on 2 containers.
Clean strawberries; cut into fourths.
Put in bowl with pineapple and 1/2 the pineapple juice. Add the glaze; mix well.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture on one angel food cake, the rest on the other.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill, then serve.
It makes 2 desserts.

title: lemon supreme special
directions: Mix together the cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar. Add one egg at a time and beat thoroughly after each addition.
Pour into a prepared Bundt pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool for 15 minutes before removing cake from pan. While the cake is still hot, brush with Lemon Glaze.

title: best bread machine bread
directions: Place water, sugar and yeast in the pan of bread machine. Let the yeast dissolve and foam for 10 minutes.
Add the oil, flour, and salt to the yeast.
Select basic or white bread setting and press start.

title: corn scallop
directions: Put corn in mixing bowl.
Add crackers and beaten eggs.
Add cheese, milk and grated onion; stir well.
Bake in greased casserole for 35 minutes in 375° oven.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: We have two recipes for Eggplant (Grandma's own).
Try them both!

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Gather young tender polk leaves.
Clean and boil in water until tender.
Drain and add turnip greens.
Cover with water. Add seasonings, a little bacon grease and salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.

title: reception salad
directions: Boil juice from the crushed pineapple and dissolve Jell-O in it.
When this is almost jelled, add the cream cheese which is at room temperature and has been mashed with a fork; mix well.
Add pineapple, celery, nuts and salt.
Fold in the cream which has been whipped stiff.

title: beef curry
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet. Saute onions over medium heat just until tender. Stir in curry or sage; cook 1 minute. Add beef cubes and next 5 ingredients in order listed. Continue cooking until beef cubes are lightly browned. Add enough water to barely cover beef. Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours until beef is tender. Thicken with cornstarch/water mixture. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken and chipped beef
directions: Wrap bacon around chicken and line a dish with chipped beef. Mix the rest of the ingredients together and pour over top.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in heavy frying pan over moderate heat.
Sprinkle with flour, stirring until each piece is well coated.
Slowly stir in broth made from bouillon cubes and water; add soy sauce.
Add celery, sliced mushrooms and onions.
Cover and cook slowly about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, to prevent sticking.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: leon's blueberry muffins
directions: In bowl at low speed, mix butter and sugar until fluffy. Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Gradually sift flour, baking powder and salt to the mixture, adding milk periodically.
Add berries; mix gently.
Fill cups well; sprinkle with sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: snicker cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Pour half of the batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels, margarine and milk.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pour remaining cake batter on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 250°, then 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost (very good without frosting).

title: honey fruit dressing for fruit
directions: Combine ingredients in small bowl; beat until smooth.
Serve over fresh fruit.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Boil 2 1/4 cups water; add to jello.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice.
Let jell in refrigerator.
Whip in cream cheese, Cool Whip, celery and drained pineapple.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg together.
Add molasses and spices. Blend in flour gradually.
Chill dough in refrigerator for 1 hour for easier handling.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll into sugar and place 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: hill drive kahlua
directions: Heat water, sugar and coffee to a boil.
Cool.
Add vanilla and brandy.
Store 3 weeks.

title: zucchini saute
directions: In a skillet or saucepan, saute zucchini in butter on medium high heat for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and saute gently 2 to 3 minutes.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: sue's monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and set aside.
Dissolve shortening, sugar and salt in boiling water; add beaten eggs and mix well.
(Bring water to boil and remove from heat; add other ingredients and let stand to melt.)
Add the two mixtures alternately to flour.
Mix well.

title: low-fat taco salad
directions: Brown turkey with onion, peppers and garlic. Drain thoroughly. Add cumin and chili powder.
Stir 3 to 4 minutes to blend flavors. Add water and 1 cup taco sauce.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Let each person assemble their own salad using the meat mixture and remaining ingredients, using the shredded Cheddar, sour cream, taco sauce and chips for toppings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to boil and continue to boil for three minutes.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on a sheet of waxed paper.

title: shrimp and vegetable egg rolls
directions: In large pot, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Cook cabbage and carrots over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes until wilted.
Stir in soy sauce.
Add garlic and ginger.
Cook 1 minute, stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in scallions, shrimp, cilantro and basil.
Put in bowl and let cool.
Cover wrappers with damp towel.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onions.
Let stand 1 hour. Drain well.
Place in a deep kettle with sugar, vinegar and spices.
Cook slowly over simmer burner until the sugar is dissolved, then turn burner up full and boil rapidly until the slices begin to glisten (about 30 minutes).
Pack in hot jars, fill with hot liquid and seal.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix in casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and celery in bowl.
Mix salad dressing, salt, poultry seasoning, onion salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and celery; toss.
Cover; chill 2 hours.
Just before serving, add mandarin oranges and grapes.

title: ima's lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add carbonated beverage and chill until partially set.
Drain pineapple and save juice; add pineapple and banana into jello.
Chill until firm.
Combine sugar and flour in saucepan.
Stir in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook over low heat until thickened; chill until cool.
Fold in whipped Dream Whip.
Ice jello with Dream Whip mixture when jello is firm.
Top with a few bits of grated cheese.

title: mocha shake
directions: Place water, cocoa, sugar, and instant coffee in blender. Cover and blend briefly on low speed.
Add milk.
Cover and blend well on high speed.
Add ice cream.
Cover and blend until smooth. Serve immediately.
Garnish as desired.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Spoon peanut butter batter in muffin pan about 3/4 full. Stir together oats, raisins, honey and butter. Spoon over batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and tater casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread ground beef in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper; sprinkle onion and spread soup over ground beef.
Cover mixture with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken in 1-inch pieces. Put chicken and next 3 ingredients together. Let stand 1 hour or refrigerate overnight.

title: pork chop and scalloped potato casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil in a large skillet.
Remove to a plate. Add onion to skillet; saute until tender.
Remove from heat; reserve.

title: egg casserole
directions: Crumble bread in a 9 X 13 pan.	Beat eggs, mustard, salt & milk.
Add cheese and pour over bread.
Fry bacon and crumble over top.
Melt oleo & pour over top of all.
Can store in refrigerator until morning & then bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beth's pizza fondue
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
In a fondue pot, add all ingredients and heat until all cheese is melted and hot.
Serve with garlic bread, cut in strips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, bread crumbs, sage and egg in bowl. Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Cook in nonstick skillet over low heat until brown on all sides. Drain!

title: chocolate delight
directions: Crumble 1/2 brownies in pretty glass bowl.
Continue to layer 1/2 of the mousse, Cool Whip, Heath bars and pecans.
Repeat layers.
Chill and enjoy.

title: fudgy peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Place first 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Combine last 4 ingredients and add to first mixture; mix well.
Pour onto greased 12 x 15 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Drizzle with frosting of powdered sugar and water until slightly warm.
Cut into bars.

title: easy italian supper
directions: In a large skillet, brown the beef.
Add Pasta Accents and spaghetti sauce.
Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and serve in the skillet.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.	Mix well.
Bake at 350°
until done, about 45 minutes.

title: pigs in cornfield
directions: Place a layer of sliced potatoes on bottom of a casserole dish.
Add a layer of sliced onions, a layer of the cream-style corn, a layer of sausage and a layer of the canned tomato soup. Cover with link pork sausage.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Open crescent rolls and lay flat on cookie sheet and press seams together.
Bake for 9 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Cool.

title: baked meatball with eggplant
directions: Blend together and shape into 18 meatballs (golf ball size). Fry in oil.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: In small saucepan, combine the cream cheese and salsa.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until melted and well blended.
Stir in chicken and pinto beans.
Fill tortillas with the mixture, roll and place into greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Spread cheese over the top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets and set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients in heavy saucepan and cook over low heat until thickened.
Pour over beets and serve warm or cold.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla and grated orange rind.
Blend in rest of ingredients; bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes in greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cucumber sandwiches(appetizer)
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill. Spread on rye snack bread.
Top with thin slice of cucumber, then sprinkle parsley flakes or seasoning salt on top.

title: broccoli and corn bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into casserole. Then sprinkle on 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted oleo.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pie crust and pie
directions: Put everything in pie pan.
Mix together, then press out with hands.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, Miracle Whip and vinegar.
Add broccoli, sunflower seeds, raisins and onion.
Seal and refrigerate overnight.
Stir and crumble bacon over top before serving.

title: lemon sheet cake
directions: First mix jello with boiling water.
Set in refrigerator. When cake is done, stick holes in cake.
Pour lemon jello over cake.
Mix 1 box powdered sugar and 1/2 cup lemon juice; spread over cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use 12 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: calico beans
directions: Saute hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat.
Fry bacon.
Drain and reserve 2 to 4 tablespoons of drippings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Stir
cornstarch into a little milk. Cook in a double boiler until mixture thickens.
After cooled, put into freezer and add sugar and cream.
Fill up freezer with milk until about 3 1/2 inches from top.
Add vanilla and salt.
Stir well and freeze.

title: homemade pear jelly
directions: Peel pears and lay in pan of water.
Shred pears and add lemon juice.
Put in thick bottom pot.
Add sugar; bring to boil.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Add whole boxes of Certo; boil for 2 minutes. Seal in warm jars with boiled jar caps.

title: pickle-roll-em-vas
directions: Spread 1 side of ham slice with 1 tablespoon cream cheese. Place 1 pickle on edge of each ham slice.
Roll ham slice around pickle.
Press edges to seal.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut each into 6 slices.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Add water to raisins and boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla and cooled raisins.
Sift and add baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add chopped nuts.
Chill and then drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: strawberry-cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add strawberries and cranberry relish. Add lemon-lime drink.
Mix and refrigerate until set.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add oil, water and pumpkin.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Makes three loaf pans.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with soyannaise.
Garnish with paprika, chopped parsley, radish roses and/or avocado slices.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter.
Add flour, grated cheese and red pepper. Mixture is very stiff and short.
Chill.
Roll on waxed paper and cut or squeeze through a cookie press.
May top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mucky duck key lime pie
directions: Mix the milk with lime juice in a large mixing bowl.
In another bowl, whip egg whites until you find you can almost turn the bowl over without them falling out.
Add egg whites to bowl with condensed milk and lime juice.
Mix slowly with a whisk so as to not deflate the whipped whites.
Pour into pie shell and freeze. Serve sliced with whipped cream.
Remove from freezer just prior to serving.

title: picadillo(seasoned ground beef)
directions: Brown chopped meat in large frying pan.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and let it cook on medium heat approximately 1/2 hour. Tastes better if warm.
Serve over white rice or put on crackers for a snack.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir together and pour into unbaked tarts.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: mrs. taylor's punch(serves 50)
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and water.
Cool to room temperature. Add juices and flavoring.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale.

title: lazy gal cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk in bowl.
Pour this mixture into melted butter.
Add fruit.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: In a medium size saucepan over moderate heat, bring the chicken broth to
a
simmer.
Add
the chicken breasts, adjust the heat so
that
the broth bubbles gently.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm.
Remove from the heat, let the breasts cool
in
the
broth
for
10 minutes, then drain, saving the broth
for
another use.
Cut the chicken meat into bite size pieces.

title: rich cake
directions: Combine brown sugar and eggs until smooth.
It may be necessary to put this over low heat until it melts together.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: one-pot dinner(green beans, potatoes and smoked sausage)
directions: Add potatoes to bean mixture and cook until done.
Cut the sausage into 1-inch sections and boil in a separate pan to remove most of the grease.
Drain and add to bean and potato mixture.

title: my mom's noodles
directions: Place egg, milk, salt and cream of tartar in food processor and mix.
Slowly add flour until mixed.
Thinly roll out on floured surface.
Cut into strips and spread out to dry.
Add to boiling water, chicken or beef broth and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch for sticking.

title: quick and easy cherry cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually add milk.
Add instant pudding and beat until well blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill.
Enjoy!

title: fresh grapefruit cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar; beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture, alternating with grapefruit juice (beginning and ending with flour mixture).
Gradually add milk.
Stir in peel and vanilla; mix well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove; let cool completely.
Frost with Grapefruit Frosting.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt and milk in a 2-quart saucepan.
Quickly bring to a boil, stirring only until sugar is dissolved.
Boil without stirring until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Lay 1 package rolls in bottom (spread to fit and pinch together).
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Lay other package of rolls on top.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, stirring until melted.
After it has slightly congealed, put in refrigerator a short while, then add fruit and nuts.
Fold in sour cream and chill until firm.

title: melting pot beans
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and cook onion and green pepper with chili powder until tender (use shortening, if necessary).
Stir to separate meat.
Add beans, macaroni, cheese, milk and salt.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Garnish with green pepper rings, if desired. Makes about 6 cups.

title: ham stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Stir the first 8 ingredients together in a bowl. Drop head of cabbage into a large pot of boiling water and start nudging off the leaves as they loosen. Divide the filling into 12 portions; roll into sausage shape and put into cabbage leaf. Saute the 1 cup sliced onions with the butter; cook until onions are translucent. In large frypan, arrange cabbage rolls in a single layer; add Italian tomatoes with juice, salt and pepper to taste. Bury the bay leaves in pan. Cover and simmer slowly, basting occasionally, for 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine ingredients and place 1/3 cup of mix in mug.
Add hot water.

title: polka dotted macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain the macaroni as directed on the package.
Empty the soup into a bowl.
Slowly stir in the milk.
Spread the drained macaroni in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Then pour the cheese sauce over the macaroni and stir to mix.
Cut the hot dogs into thin slices and arrange them on top of the macaroni and cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 375° or until hot and bubbly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach cheese bake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir until well blended.
Spoon mixture into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; top with Cheddar cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil
and	sugar
together.
Add
eggs; beat well. Sift flour, salt,
cocoa
and soda together.
Add red coloring and flavoring
to
sugar
mixture.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.	Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat with onions and peppers and drain.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Shake oil, lemon juice, soy sauce and brown sugar in tightly covered jar.
Twist top from pineapple; cut pineapple into fourths.
Cut fruit from rind; remove core and any "eyes."
Slice each fourth lengthwise; cut crosswise into chunks.
Toss pineapple chunks, apple and green onion with dressing.
Place romaine in shallow bowl; mound fruit mixture in center.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef until it loses pink color.
Over beef mixture spread soup, noodles, zucchini and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, until noodles are done.
Stir in sour cream and heat. Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and mix in chocolate.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and mix.
Add nuts and mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Use a 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: baked potato in a pan
directions: Peel, cube, and boil potatoes in salted water until done. Drain well and mash potatoes; add butter, salt, pepper, and 1/2 cup cheese; stir.
Add bacon bits and sour cream; stir well and pour in a Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350 degrees until cheese melts.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Place candy bar, marshmallows and milk in heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted and the mixture is smooth. Cool....

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Add sliced potatoes; simmer until potatoes are tender.
Top with cheese of your choice.
Cover until cheese is melted.

title: spice bars
directions: Mix together and press into a coating sprayed cookie sheet or jelly roll pan with 1/2-inch sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and glaze while hot.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Saute seasonings in butter.
Add all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into large casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate coconut drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat and stir in milk, coconut and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Place in oven and turn off heat.
Leave in oven for about 15 minutes or until cookies have glazed appearance.
While warm, remove from cookie sheet.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes, then top with potato chips. Bake the last 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Shape above ingredients in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease an 11-inch iron skillet with Crisco solid shortening. Shake 1 tablespoon meal around on bottom. Put corn bread mix in the cold skillet and bake 48 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.

title: frozen punch
directions: Thaw orange juice and lemonade.
Do not dilute.
Mix together and add pineapple juice.
Freeze in cardboard milk carton. Several hours before serving, set out to soften.
Tear off carton, put in punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Will be slushy.
Good for a hot evening.

title: doughnuts
directions: Fry in hot grease and roll in sugar.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, oleo and sugar together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Mix well.
Spread on cooled crust. Mix gelatin with water, then add frozen berries.
Stir until berries soften and gelatin starts to thicken.
Gently pour or spread mixture on top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar, vinegar and vanilla.
Add eggs, raisins, pecans and coconut.
Pour into a pie crust and bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix and form into a ball.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: pantry casserole
directions: Place asparagus in casserole dish, then English peas and mushrooms.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over top, then sprinkle grated cheese on top of soup.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.

title: party cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and continue creaming until very fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until light.
Sift flour; measure.
Add salt and baking powder and sift twice more.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add dry and liquid ingredients alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Top with favorite frosting.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the first 4 ingredients.
Boil 1 minute.
Add salt, pecans and vanilla.
Dump in buttered pan.

title: pita chips
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Split each of 6 pita breads into 2 round pieces.
Cut each half into 6 triangles with kitchen shears. Arrange in single layers on cookie sheets.
Spray with vegetable spray.
Lightly sprinkle with garlic salt or powder, if desired. Bake for 8 minutes until chips are lightly browned and crisp. Store in a tight container.
Makes 8 cups.

title: potatoes chantilly
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in half.	Cook in boiling, salted water until soft, but not mushy.	Drain.	Rub potatoes through sieve. Return to pan and work with wooden spoon until smooth. Add margarine and salt and pepper
to
taste.
Add
hot
milk until desired consistency is obtained.
Beat until fluffy.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Blend cheese and milk; stir in beef, onion, green pepper and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Spoon into an 8-inch glass pie plate.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at
350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with "Bugles."
Can be mixed and refrigerated in a bowl prior to baking in pie plate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix all cheeses together.
Add Tabasco and garlic to suit taste.

title: orange rice
directions: Place juice and milk in a medium sized heavy saucepan and bring to a boil over moderately high heat.
Mixture will curdle. Stir rice and salt into boiling milk mixture and when it returns to a boil, turn heat to low.
Cover pan and cook 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Transfer cooked rice to a serving bowl. Cover and chill several hours.
Place yogurt and sugar in a small mixing bowl and mix.
Add to rice.
Add diced oranges and stir gently to combine all ingredients.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crock-pot beef casserole
directions: Place roast in bottom of pot and then halved potatoes, celery, and carrots.
Cover with soup.
Add water.
Salt as desired.
Cook slowly approximately 6 to 7 hours on low.

title: christmas a.m. casserole
directions: First Layer:
6 pieces bread, 1/2 cup cooked sausage, 1/2 egg, milk mixture and 1/2 of cheese; repeat layer.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar and a pinch of salt.
Beat egg yolks. Add the juice and grated rind of 1 lemon.
Then add flour and sugar continuing to beat.
Stir in milk and lastly fold in egg whites beaten stiff, but not dry.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan or 2 round layer pans.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar, shortening, eggs, and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda, cloves, and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in bananas, oats, and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375°F for 10-12 min.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer in order as given.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir when ready to serve.

title: my secret potato salad
directions: Do not overcook diced potatoes.
Drain.
Run cold water over them to cool real good.
Add all ingredients together and toss. Add salt, pepper and seasoning salt to taste.
Add mayonnaise as needed.
Sprinkle paprika generously on top.
Put in dish of your choice.

title: nona roscana's yourta
directions: The amount of vegetables depends on how many servings you are making. Use a glass baking dish, size appropriate for number of servings. Grease dish with shortening or spray with Pam. Layer vegetables, starting with potatoes. Between each set of vegetable layers, drizzle small amount of olive oil, add salt and pepper and sprinkle Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° until potatoes are fork tender, about 45 minutes. Cover to cook, then uncover last 10 minutes to brown.

title: hot cornbread
directions: Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 500° until done.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and instant pudding.
Add 3/4 cup oil, water and eggs.
Beat 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for about 1 hour at 325°.
While cake is baking, mix together confectioners sugar and 2 tablespoons oil and orange juice.
When cake is done, punch holes closely all over the top (while cake is warm).
Pour mixture over the hot cake. Cover cake with lid or tinfoil.
Let stand until thoroughly cold (3 to 4 hours).
Store in refrigerator until serving time.

title: cream cheese cakes
directions: Beat above ingredients, except vanilla wafers, until smooth. Put Sunshine vanilla wafers upside down in paper cups (in small muffin pans).
Fill almost to top.
Bake at 350° on middle rack for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.
Top with Thank You pie filling.

title: special hamburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Form patties and fry or bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: black moons
directions: Mix ingredients in one bowl.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 7 minutes.

title: mom's enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry hamburger and chopped onion and drain. Mix soup, sour cream, green chillies and cheese into meat mixture while it's still hot.
Set aside.
Fry tortillas in oil to soften. Assemble in long/high sided baking dish.
Fill each tortilla with meat mixture and roll up.
Fill pan with rolled up tortillas.
Put any leftover meat over top and some grated cheese, too.
Bake until nice and brown, about 1 hour.

title: mild salsa
directions: Chop a can of whole tomatoes and put them in a bowl with the juice.
Chop some parsley; add olive oil and Tabasco sauce.
Chop some onions, only if you like them, and put all of these in the tomatoes.
Now you are ready to eat them with corn chips.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add flour to sugar and mix, then add to margarine.
Beat egg yolks and add all other ingredients to mixture.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: no crust cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and grease an 8 x 12-inch glass ovenproof dish.
Beat until creamy the eggs, 1 1/2 cups of sugar, cream cheese and 2 teaspoons of
vanilla.
Pour into dish and bake in a 325° oven until you can touch center and it's not soft, 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set 10 minutes.

title: merry christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool until syrupy, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into a round 8-inch or 9 x 1 1/2-inch cake pan lined with wax paper.
Chill until firm, turn out on waxed paper and frost top.
Cutting wedges on lettuce, decorate squares with cranberry sauce and walnut halves.

title: never-fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil milk and sugar 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into greased dish to set until firm.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix first five ingredients and add 1/3 c. oil very slowly. Add 1 c. oil slowly after mixing other ingredients together and beat.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in the refrigerator.
A blender works best to mix this.

title: brownies
directions: Microwave margarine until melted. Mix in other ingredients. Mix well. Put in 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat vigorously.
Put in greased 8-inch square, 9-inch square or 6 x 10-inch pan.
Drain cherries. Put cherries over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar. Pour 1 cup hot water or hot cherry juice over all.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Good served warm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add liquids.
Mix and bake at 350° for one hour in layer pan.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate in covered bowl.
This is good when you have a number of people to serve.

title: cocoa fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Melt butter.
Stir together sugar, flour, cocoa powder, soda and salt.
Add to batter with oil.
Stir until smooth.

title: bryan bacon vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator at least 5 hours.
Best when made one day before use to allow flavors to combine.
Yields 1 cup.

title: hot mustard
directions: Mix mustard with water to make a paste and set aside. Boil all but mustard mix.
Cook 5 minutes and cool.
Add mustard mix and beat with electric mixer for 5 minutes.

title: tomato supreme
directions: Scald tomatoes; remove skin and centers.
Sprinkle inside of tomato with salt and chill in refrigerator.
Mix cheese, cream, chili sauce, catsup, paprika, salt and pepper together into a thick, smooth cream.
Fill the tomatoes mixture and return to refrigerator until ready to serve.
Top with mayonnaise (a drop). Serve on a small leaf of lettuce.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Combine the 3 ingredients. Work in sausage and cheese well. Drop and shape on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until nice and brown. Serve hot.
These freeze well.

title: peach and raisin pudding
directions: Mix beaten eggs, milk and peach juice.
Dip slices of bread into the mixture.
Arrange slices in an oval pie dish so that they overlap.
Put peaches between and on top.
Pour remaining juice over mixture.
Sprinkle generously with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until set and gently brown. Dust with 4x sugar.
Serve with cream of yogurt.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Beat eggs in mixer.
Mix sugar and flour together, then add to eggs.
When foamy, fold in rhubarb.
Pour into pie crust.
Make lattice top and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: hobo supper
directions: Peel and cut potatoes and carrots in strips. Put butter in bottom of pan.
Mix potatoes and carrots.
Put in pan.
Add chops. Season to taste.

title: melting moments
directions: Cream Butter and sugar until fluffy. Blend in flour gradually and beat at medium 5 minutes. Chill overnight.

title: annapolis salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup pineapple juice. Bring remaining juice to a boil; pour over gelatin.
Put aside to cool.
Mix pineapple (cut into small pieces), nuts, celery, green peppers and salt with cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Add cooled gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into ring mold, rinsed with cold water.
Chill until firm.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Cook leek in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except light cream, parsley and green onion.
Cook until potatoes are very soft.
Blend.
Reheat with light cream.
Serve with minced parsley and chopped green onion.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Heat
vinegar,	oil
and
sweetener to boil.
Pour over peas, onion and bell pepper.
Let set for a good spell.

title: sour cream waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks in a large bowl.
Beat in milk, melted butter, vanilla and sour cream.
Combine flour, salt and other dry ingredients.
Sift into egg mixture and beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Carefully fold into batter.
Bake and serve with desired topping.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put contents of chicken in roaster.
Pour all soups and rice over chicken.
Dot each piece of chicken with butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 300° to 350° until done.
Make gravy with drippings.

title: church lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and oil; save 1 cup for crumbs.
Pat remaining mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crisp chocolate-raisin bars
directions: Line loaf pan with waxed paper to overlap sides of pan.
In a 1-quart bowl, add chocolate and peanut butter.
Microwave until melted.
Add cereal and raisins.
Mix.
Pour into pan and press to flatten.
Put into freezer for 1 hour.
Store in freezer.
Makes 8 bars (1/2 fruit, 1/2 protein, 1/2 fat and 60 optional calories).

title: old-fashioned sour cream cookies
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add cream and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.
Do not overbake.

title: fig muffins(one dozen servings)
directions: Soak figs in sherry wine for 1 hour.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs. Mix flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add with oil mixture to figs.
Can be baked in loaf pan 1 hour or in muffin tin at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: new salad
directions: Mix together cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with dry jello.
Add drained pineapple, mandarin oranges, coconut and nuts (optional).
You may substitute any fruit and dry jello.
Quick and easy.

title: cheesy baked potatoes
directions: Mix and bake at 300°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: squash and carrot casserole
directions: Cook squash and carrots separately and drain both well. Season to taste.
Melt oleo and add to the bread stuffing.
Mix sour cream and chicken soup together.
Put half of the bread stuffing mix in the bottom of baking dish; place squash and carrots on top of crumbs and add the soup mixture.
Put remainder of crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: diet pie
directions: Mix all ingredients
together.	Put
in pie crust.
Top this with the fruit and	put
in the refrigerator for 3 hours. Slice and serve cold.

title: ground beef hot dish
directions: Brown meat, onions and peppers in large skillet.
Stir in water, catsup and mustard.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from fire and let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover.
Let stand until cheese is melted.
Garnish with lettuce leaves, pickle and tomato slices.

title: poor man's quiche
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a deep 12-inch pie plate.
Mix veggies and cheese together and place in pie plate.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over veggies.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple ring coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl. Stir in walnuts and set aside. Combine sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs. Stir in apples. Stir apple mixture into flour mixture just until moistened (will seem very stiff). Spoon into greased 10-inch tube pan; spread evenly. Bake in preheated 325° oven 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool cake in pan on wire rack 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven; cool completely on wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, cherries and juice.
Mix salt and baking powder with flour; add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Put in well-greased loaf tin and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cherry-cola salad
directions: Bring the 3/4 cup
sugar
and
3/4 cup water to a boil. Add 1 can cherry pie filling and bring to a boil.
Pour boiled mixture over 1
large
box
cherry
Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple (drained), chopped walnuts and cola.
Stir well and chill until set.

title: pancakes
directions: *If self-rising flour is used, omit salt and baking powder.

title: breadstick knots
directions: About 1 hour before serving: preheat oven to 350°, grease large cookie sheet.
Separate breadsticks from one container, tie each piece into a knot and place about 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg white and sprinkle with half of poppy seeds. Repeat with rest of dough.

title: great barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat until sugar is dissolved and sauce is hot.
Excellent for either chicken or pork.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Cook bread crumbs and milk in a double boiler 12 minutes. Remove from heat and add beaten eggs.
Flake the salmon, removing bones.
Add salmon and remaining ingredients to bread crumbs and milk.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Set dish in pan of hot water and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven until firm in center when pressed gently or until knife comes out clean.

title: celery & water chestnut casserole
directions: Cut up celery and boil in salt water for 7 minutes.
Drain and add the can of cream of chicken soup and one cup water chestnuts (drained and sliced thin).
Put in casserole dish.
Melt one stick oleo, add crackers and slivered almonds to oleo.
Put cracker mixture on top of celery & water chestnut mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut; if using canned sprouts, drain also.
Mix vinegar and sugar; simmer until sugar dissolves.
Add to vegetables.
Chill overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Place back in cooking pot. Add onions and green pepper (may puree if wish).
Then add dry ingredients followed by tomato ingredients.
Simmer mixture on low 2 to 4 hours.

title: curry chicken
directions: Cut Chicken in small pieces.
Combine Chicken, Curry Powder, Black Pepper, Seasoned Salt, Garlic Powder and Onion Powder in a a large bowl.
Cover and mix well.
On top of stove in a large sauce pan, put in Oil and add Chicken.
On low, stir every 10 minutes for at least one hour or until tender.
Serve with white rice.

title: simple white pouring sauce
directions: Cook all, except butter and mushrooms.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter.
Add mushrooms.
Ready to serve.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix salmon, egg, bread and saltines in large bowl.
Crush corn flakes in separate bowl.
Roll salmon patties in corn flakes and bake in oven until browned.

title: festive fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup fluted tube pan. In large bowl, combine eggs and water.
Add remaining ingredients, except corn syrup; stir by hand until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes, or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool in pan 30 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Wrap in plastic or foil and store in refrigerator.
Glaze with warm corn syrup before serving, if desired.

title: chicken & noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine mayonnaise and Italian dressing. Fold together all ingredients until evenly blended.
Chill well. Serves 6.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Fry meat until brown in butter.
Chop garlic fine.
Add to meat.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and sauce to meat.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Start oven at 350°.
Chop onions and some green tops.
Mix with cream cheese and sour cream.
Put 1/3 of noodles in casserole.
Spread 1/3 cream mixture.
Cover with 1/3 meat mixture.
Repeat until 3 layers each.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until bubbling.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: Combine sausage and celery in a large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until sausage is browned and celery is tender.
Stir to crumble meat.
Drain.
Stir in chicken broth, mushroom soup, chicken soup, water chestnuts, mushrooms, rice and thyme.
Mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 3- quart casserole and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours. Garnish with parsley if desired.

title: kathy's brownies
directions: Combine 1st three ingredients; add melted chocolate and vanilla. Mix well. Add flour and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: velveeta cheese dip
directions: Mix together and serve with your favorite chips.

title: blizzard
directions: Place milk and candy into blender with ice cream.
Blend until smooth.

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a bowl.
Slowly add milk and vanilla; beat well.
Melt butter and add to batter.
Pour fruit and juice into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Dump batter into fruit; do not stir.
Bake in a 375° oven about 45 minutes or until brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: extra-lite egg casserole
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Coat bread in oleo and place in dish. Mix together milk, salt, pepper and Egg Beaters. Pour over bread. Sprinkle shredded cheese over mixture. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: dream whip pie
directions: Mix together and press in bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, milk and sugar.
Pour into baking dish with the melted butter.
Pour 2 cups of fruit and juice on top and bake. Do not stir.

title: no-fat cookies
directions: Mix together the mashed bananas, egg whites and dates.
Add oats and raisins.
Place on cookie sheet by tablespoonfuls and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: my award winning pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar until light. Add eggs and flour alternately, then add flavorings. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: baked rice
directions: Melt butter with rice.
Combine other ingredients and pour into large casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pudding cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Set aside 1/4 cup coconut.
Stir remaining coconut into batter.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan. When completely cool, brush top of cake with honey and sprinkle reserved coconut.

title: slurch
directions: Slurch won't hold a shape like play dough.
Wonderful play medium for young ooze-enthusiasts!
Ok for the littlest kids.

title: frozen strawberries
directions: Boil water and Sure-Jell and add sugar.
Pour over berries in containers and freeze.

title: dill pickled okra
directions: Scrub okra and pack whole pods into clean, hot jars.
In each jar, insert a few celery leaves, 1 garlic clove, peeled and 1 sprig of dill.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour the boiling liquid over the okra.
Seal.
Process 10 minutes in simmering hot water bath.
Let okra stand for about 1 month before using.
(To can in quart jars, increase the processing time by 5 minutes.)
Makes 4 pints.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add marshmallows and let melt.
Add drained pineapple; let chill until thickened, about 1 1/2 hours.
Fold in whipped cream, cottage cheese and nuts.
Pour into jello mold.

title: spinach salad with chutney dressing
directions: Chicken may be added to make a main course salad.

title: cornstarch gravy
directions: Pour off drippings and return 2 tablespoons to roasting pan. Stir in broth. Cook over medium heat, stirring to loosen browned bits from bottom of pan.
Remove from heat and add milk.
Mix cornstarch and cold water until smooth.
Add to liquid in pan. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Makes about 2 cups gravy. Can be made in saucepan.

title: haystacks(candy)
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
Add the rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: ham and egg bake
directions: Beat eggs, milk, mustard and garlic salt.
Sprinkle flour over cheese and stir.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan. Put bread slices on bottom.
Add chopped ham, onion and cheese over bread. Pour egg mixture over top.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffed sewer pipes
directions: Brown ground meat in oil.
Drain and add salt, pepper, onion and garlic salt.
Add spinach.
Drain spinach and cut up spinach. Brown again on low heat.
Add bread crumbs or crackers.
Add mushrooms and egg; mix well.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Turn heat off.

title: kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until they foam.
Add vanilla and vinegar. Beat stiff.
Add sugar gradually, one teaspoon at a time.
Bake on waxed paper on inverted pan at 150° to 175° for one hour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown onion in oil.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Add green beans and soup. Pour into casserole.
Mash potatoes with milk and egg.
Spoon over meat mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy quiche
directions: Cook vegetables.
Drain and add onion.
Bake empty crust for 5 minutes at 425°.
Remove crust from oven and place vegetables, ham and cheese in crust.
Beat together eggs, milk and salt and pour over vegetables.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
This freezes well in the pan.

title: orange dip
directions: Combine orange juice and milk in a mixing bowl.
Add pudding, seal bowl and shake for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream. Chill 2 hours.
Serve with any fruit.

title: bon bons
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar, milk, pecans and coconut until well mixed.
Roll into balls, refrigerate 2 hours or overnight. Mix chocolate chips and paraffin in a double-broiler, dip balls and place on wax paper.

title: sara's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and chop to bite size pieces.
Boil eggs; save yolks and chop whites.
Mix mayonnaise, egg yolks and pickle juice to taste.
Coat potatoes, egg whites, pickles, celery and onions with yolk mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut blossom candy
directions: Mix the 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Roll into balls. May be eaten as is or topped with a Hershey's Kiss pushed down slightly to make a blossom.
They can also be dipped in chocolate.

title: christmas porridge
directions: Toast almonds.
Cook barley in 2 quarts water.
Boil 45 minutes over medium heat.
Add fruits and the rest of ingredients. Cook until thick.
Serve with cream.

title: hard or rock candy
directions: Cook and stir Karo syrup, sugar and water in saucepan over medium heat to dissolve sugar, then cook, without stirring, to 300° or until a small mixture separates into hard brittle threads in very cold water.
Cool a minute, stirring flavoring and food coloring (if wanted).
Pour into a cookie sheet or any pan.
Let harden.
After candy is hard, break with a knife.
Candy is ready to eat.

title: steak diane
directions: Sprinkle steaks with salt and pepper.
Saute in clarified butter until they are light brown.
Add the sherry and cognac and set on fire.
When blaze subsides, remove steaks to warm platter. Do not pour off liquid in pan.
Squeeze lemon juice into pan. Then add mustard, parsley, chives and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well and heat to bubbly.
Spoon over steaks.
Enjoy!!

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Heat milk.
Mix flour, sugar and salt, then stir into milk slowly.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks which have been slightly beaten and oleo; continue cooking for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell (will fill an 8-inch pan).
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: chicken and broccoli stir-fry(lo-cal)
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute garlic and vegetables in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes, or until done.
Add cooked rice.

title: siamese chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake 1 1/4 hours in 350° oven.
Serve with rice.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend for 30 seconds, or until ice cubes are crushed.

title: brush pile pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a little oil, then remove from skillet. Pour in rice.
Brown rice in drippings, stirring often.
Pour in soup.
Mix with the rice.
Return pork chops to skillet and add enough water to cover the chops.
Cover.
Cook until pork chops are tender.

title: debbie's butterscotch cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In medium saucepan, melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts. Press half the mixture firmly into bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk, vanilla and egg.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool to warm temperature.
Chill before cutting into bars.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar until all sugar grains disappear.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time and beat well after each egg.
Mix soda and hot water; add to batter.
Add buttermilk with 1/2 teaspoon salt stirred in alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: cucumber soup
directions: In blender, place the first 6 ingredients; blend on high for 20 seconds.
In double boiler, melt the butter and flour.
Pour in cucumber mixture and heat.
Take off fire.
Add the cream or milk and finely chopped cucumbers.
Chill.

title: creamy broccoli-raisin salad
directions: Remove broccoli leaves and cut off tough ends of the stalks. Wash broccoli thoroughly and break flowerets into small or bite size pieces.

title: spectacular squash
directions: Combine the stuffing mix with melted butter and press half of it into 9 x 13-inch or 3-quart casserole dish. Lightly steam squash and onion until barely cooked. Drain thoroughly. Combine soup, sour cream and grated carrot. Fold in cooked squash and onions. Gently spoon mixture over stuffing mix in casserole dish and top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° until stuffing mix begins to brown and casserole bubbles around edge, about 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 10. Can do ahead. Don't freeze.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients,
except
onion
rings, and bake at 350° until heated through, covered.
Then uncover and top with onion rings.
Bake another 5 or 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
In separate saucepan, melt margarine.
Mix in flour and milk.
Stir to combine. Add Velveeta and reduce heat to "low."
Stir constantly until all cheese is melted.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Simmer celery in small amount of water until tender and drained.
Combine macaroni and rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Slice English muffins in half.
Spread on pizza sauce.
Put on a few pepperonis and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Place pizzas on a cookie sheet and heat at 350° until brown.

title: kahuileipa(finnish coffee bread)
directions: Heat milk.
Stir in 3 cups flour and then yeast, dissolved in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Let rise 1 hour.
Add sugar, egg yolks and remaining flour.
Knead well 15 minutes or until dough leaves hands.
Let rise again until double its size.
Make into loaves and put into greased pans.
Let rise again (1 hour).
Brush tops with beaten egg before putting into 375° oven.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package, making 2 (8-inch) layers.
When cool, split both layers horizontally.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers of cake.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple and strawberries. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish; chill until set.
Combine pudding mix and milk; beat with electric mixer until thickened. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over congealed mixture and chill until serving time.

title: white chocolate raspberry cheesecake
directions: Mix and press into 9-inch spring-form pan and set aside.

title: whole wheat peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll in balls and drop on baking sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pastry pancakes
directions: Stir dry ingredients together in a bowl large enough to accommodate the liquid ingredients.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix
well,
knead.
Let
raise
for 1 hour.
Work down. Put in refrigerator overnight.
Take out and put in pans.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours or until light.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potatoes with skin until soft.
Remove skin and mash potatoes.
Add sugar and mix until you have the consistency of stiff dough.
Turn onto board or waxed paper and roll out until you have a thin layer.
Spread a layer of peanut butter on top. Roll up into a long roll and slice about 1/2 inch thick.
Let set until firm.

title: english toffee
directions: Boil butter, sugar and water to 300° or until the color of peanut butter (dark).
Spread nuts on buttered cookie sheet with sides.
Pour hot mixture evenly over nuts.
Break chocolate bar into pieces and lay over hot mixture; spread lightly with a knife to cover evenly.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: holiday grape dressing
directions: Brown rice in oil; remove from skillet and set aside.
Cook and stir onions and celery in same skillet.
Stir in mushrooms, broth, rice and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is cooked and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in grapes, nuts and parsley; cook about 2 minutes or until grapes are thoroughly heated.

title: holiday nuts
directions: Bring water to boil in medium kettle.
Add nuts and boil 1 minute.
Drain and return to kettle.
Add sugar.
Stir until well coated.
Heat enough oil in large frying pan to cover about 1/2-inch.
When hot, add nuts and fry until all steam has stopped, stirring constantly.
Spoon nuts on absorbent paper towels or newspaper.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cool completely.

title: flaky pie crust(makes 6)
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients until consistency of coarse meal.
Add enough water to vinegar and egg to make 1 cup. Add liquid to mixture until dough forms a ball.
Divide dough and pat out with hands and roll into 9-inch crusts.
Pastry will keep several months in freezer if wrapped tightly.
The dough may be left in dough balls and frozen.
I use Ziploc freezer bags.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix meal, beaten eggs, sweet milk, soda, salt, corn and bacon drippings; set aside.
Saute ground meat; put on towel and dry. Grease large iron skillet; set aside.
Pour 1/2 of batter in skillet.
Sprinkle cheese, meat, onion and peppers evenly on batter.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a 4-quart microwave-proof bowl, mix sugar, milk and butter. Cook on High 20 to 22 minutes or until mixture reaches 234° on candy thermometer, stirring every 5 minutes.
Stir chocolate and marshmallow cream until well blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
If you want thinner pieces, use a larger pan.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Put rice in bottom of roasting pan.
Mix together cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups with the water and pour over rice.
Layer chicken pieces on top and the onion soup sprinkled on top of the chicken.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove cover and continue baking for 30 more minutes.

title: molasses ginger cookies
directions: Mix.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar to coat.
Bake in a 375° oven on greased cookie sheet for 12 minutes.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggs.
Toss lightly.
Place in serving bowl.
Garnish with egg slices.
Chill.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Lightly cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine broccoli and onion with butter, eggs, Cheddar cheese and cornbread mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden.
Cut into squares.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: grandma rose's raisin pie
directions: Spread raisins directly into uncooked pie shell.
Mix together flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over raisins.
Pour milk over raisins.
Dot with the margarine.
Bake at 400° until set, 40 to 60 minutes.

title: egg noodles
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, sour cream and a large pinch of salt.
Stir until well mixed.
Add enough flour to make a soft, pliable dough.
After the first 3 cups, add flour 1/2 cup at a time.
The last addition of flour will be done while kneading the dough.
Knead just until the dough is smooth.
Let rest for 10 minutes.
Divide dough into quarters.
Roll each out on a floured surface.
Roll to a thickness of 1/8-inch.
Cut in strips and place in a pot of boiling water to cook.
When noodles rise to the top and are tender (approximately after 10 minutes), remove from the water and serve with onions sauteed in butter.

title: banana chocolate loaf
directions: Cream together the butter or margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Add the eggs and salt and mix well.
Dissolve the baking powder and baking soda in the sour cream and add to the creamed mixture. Stir in the bananas.
Gradually add the flour, vanilla and the chocolate bits.
Pour into a well buttered and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: venetian pasta rolls
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in 1/2 cup sauce and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
